{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486805030,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffe83jWKFM65pCjvi","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_4SZgEHj4z1U9qOHnR1ijRrUy","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":300},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Strategy - gpt55-fast-3\n2: \n3: ## 1. TOPIC\n4: Validate and stress-test the merge design for folding `deep-loop-runtime` into `deep-loop-workflows` as `system-deep-loop`: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether `fallback-router.ts` should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n5: \n6: ---\n7: \n8: <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n9: ## 2. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n10: - [ ] Is the proposed `system-deep-loop/runtime/` structural layout correct, especially treating runtime as infrastructure rather than a workflow mode?\n11: - [ ] Are the forward and reverse relative-path repair rules correct at concrete call sites, or do any file-depth classes break the plan?\n12: - [ ] Is the `system-spec-kit` TypeScript tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped and sufficient, or does it create a silent test-coverage gap?\n13: - [ ] Is the external reference migration complete and safely staged across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, and graph metadata?\n14: - [ ] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, deferred, or rejected for scope/behavior reasons?\n15: <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## 3. NON-GOALS\n20: - Do not execute the merge, rename, reference rewrite, or fallback-router implementation.\n21: - Do not modify files outside this detached lineage artifact directory.\n22: - Do not evaluate historical `.opencode/specs/**` references as actionable migration targets unless they affect current routing or validation.\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: ## 4. STOP CONDITIONS\n27: - Stop after legal convergence once the five key questions have evidence-backed answers and at least three iterations are complete.\n28: - Stop at `maxIterations: 10` if convergence does not occur.\n29: - Stop early only for unrecoverable state corruption inside this lineage artifact directory.\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n34: ## 5. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n35: [None yet]\n36: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n37: \n38: ---\n39: \n40: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n41: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n42: ## 6. WHAT WORKED\n43: [None yet]\n44: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n45: \n46: ---\n47: \n48: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n49: ## 7. WHAT FAILED\n50: [None yet]\n51: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n56: ## 8. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n57: [None yet]\n58: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n63: ## 9. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n64: [None yet]\n65: <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n66: \n67: ---\n68: \n69: <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n70: ## 10. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n71: [None yet]\n72: <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n77: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n78: Iteration 1: Validate the proposed physical layout and internal path-coupling repair rules against the actual current files.\n79: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n80: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n81: \n82: ---\n83: \n84: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n85: - `r