Line 3: > First release-cleanup pass on the deep-loop-runtime skill. Documentation-only changes. No code, scripts, tests or storage touched.\n\n  Line 9: The deep-loop-runtime v1.0.0 baseline shipped the arc-118 FULL_ISOLATE_NO_MCP consolidation but the documentation surface had never been audited end to end against the current sk-doc templates or HVR voice standards. The README was undersized at 174 LOC with only 6 of the 9 sections that the system-spec-kit README structural anchor prescribes. The SKILL.md frontmatter description was 240 chars (over the 130-char skill limit). Two artifacts (SKILL.md and README.md) carried a broken changelog path reference (`v1.0.0.md` instead of `v1.0.0.0.md`). A top-level `## Council Primitives` H2 inside section 3 broke the numbered-H2-ALL-CAPS rule.\n\n  Line 11: v1.1.0.0 is the first cleanup pass that addresses all four P1 doc-class deviations with surgical edits while preserving the Smart Router section, the runtime lib code, the script entry points, the tests and the SQLite storage exactly as they shipped in v1.0.0. The release ships from the `001-deep-loop-runtime` packet under `000-release-cleanup` (first of five sibling cleanup packets that follow the same template).\n\n  Line 19: The README was rewritten from 174 LOC to 470 LOC. The new structure follows the system-spec-kit 9-section pattern (OVERVIEW, QUICK START, FEATURES with 7 sub-domains, STRUCTURE, CONFIGURATION, USAGE EXAMPLES, TROUBLESHOOTING, FAQ, RELATED DOCUMENTS). The voice is anchored at ~70% of `Public/README.md` intensity. HVR self-scoring caught zero em dashes, zero prose semicolons, zero banned metaphors, zero setup-language patterns and zero copula-avoidance constructions. `validate_document.py --type readme` exits 0.\n\n  Line 53: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md` | Full rewrite. 174 LOC -> 470 LOC. New sections: OVERVIEW (How It Compares, Requirements), CONFIGURATION, USAGE EXAMPLES, TROUBLESHOOTING, FAQ. Existing sections expanded to cover all 7 runtime domains plus council primitives plus storage. |\n\n  Line 54: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md` | Three surgical edits per AF-0001 / AF-0003 / AF-0004. Smart Router section 2 preserved. Version `1.0.0` -> `1.1.0`. |\n\n  Line 55: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md` | This file. New entry conforming to `schemas/changelog-entry.schema.json` (first changelog entry to carry conforming frontmatter). |\n\n  Line 63: No consumer action required. The script-interface contract (argv shape, stdout JSON shape, exit codes) is unchanged. TS import paths into `lib/` are unchanged. The SQLite schema is unchanged at version 2. `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts` glob still picks up tests at `../deep-loop-runtime/tests/`.\n\n  Line 71: - **Spec folder**: `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/116-deep-skill-evolution/000-release-cleanup/001-deep-loop-runtime/`\n\n  Line 72: - **Audit findings ledger**: `.../001-deep-loop-runtime/findings/audit-findings.jsonl` (21 findings, 0 P0 / 6 P1 / 15 P2)\n\n  Line 73: - **Audit summary**: `.../001-deep-loop-runtime/findings/audit-summary.md`\n\n  Line 74: - **Decision records**: `.../001-deep-loop-runtime/decision-record.md` (ADR-001 Level 3, ADR-002 all-cli-devin phase 5, ADR-003 assets absent, ADR-004 no-code-edit boundary, ADR-005 resource-map.md canonical)\n\n  Line 75: - **Validation report**: `.../001-deep-loop-runtime/validation/validation-report.md` (phase 4 output, post-rewrite)\n\n  Line 78: - **Structural anchor**: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/README.md` (9-section pattern)\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/integration_points.md:\n  Line 3: description: Consumer catalog for deep-review, deep-research, doctor, system-code-graph, tests, and script call shapes that depend on deep-loop-runtime.\n\n  Line 6:   - \"deep-review deep-loop-runtime\"\n\n  Line 7:   - \"deep-research d