low mode.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:12\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:19\"]},{\"id\":\"f002-forward-rule-mostly-correct\",\"summary\":\"Forward runtime-to-hub shared references keep hop-count and delete the old sibling segment.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs:8\"]},{\"id\":\"f003-render-root-depth-missed\",\"summary\":\"render-command-contract.cjs has a WORKSPACE_ROOT depth constant that must gain one more parent hop after nesting.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs:13\"]},{\"id\":\"f004-reverse-rule-confirmed\",\"summary\":\"Workflow packet code moves one hop closer to runtime and should target ../../runtime or ../../../runtime depending on nested depth.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:14\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs:122\"]},{\"id\":\"f005-tooling-borrow-load-bearing\",\"summary\":\"Runtime typecheck and system-spec-kit council test discovery both rely on deep-loop-runtime paths and must be repaired in the structural phase.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/package.json:10\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts:18\"]}],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Add runtime as a workflow mode\",\"reason\":\"The live registry treats runtime as backendKind/runtimeLoopType infrastructure, while user-facing modes remain research/review/council/improvement.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:19\"}],\"recommendedNextFocus\":\"Inventory external reference migration categories and stress-test child 003 coverage.\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:01:18Z\",\"durationMs\":377000,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-3-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n","additions":1,"deletions":0},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-strategy.md","relativePath":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-strategy.md","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -6,11 +6,11 @@\n ---\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n ## 2. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n-- [ ] Is the proposed `system-deep-loop/runtime/` structural layout correct, especially treating runtime as infrastructure rather than a workflow mode?\n-- [ ] Are the forward and reverse relative-path repair rules correct at concrete call sites, or do any file-depth classes break the plan?\n-- [ ] Is the `system-spec-kit` TypeScript tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped and sufficient, or does it create a silent test-coverage gap?\n+- [x] Is the proposed `system-deep-loop/runtime/` structural layout correct, especially treating runtime as infrastructure rather than a workflow mode?\n+- [x] Are the forward and reverse relative-path repair rules correct at concrete call sites, or do any file-depth classes break the plan?\n+- [x] Is the `system-spec-kit` TypeScript tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped and sufficient, or does it create a silent test-coverage gap?\n - [ ] Is the external reference migration complete and safely staged across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, and graph metadata?\n - [ ] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, deferred, or rejected for scope/behavior reasons?\n <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n \n@@ -31,24 +31,27 @@\n ---\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n ## 5. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n-[None yet]\n+- Runtime should be nested under `system-deep-loop/runtime/` as infrastructure, not added to `mode-registry.json` as a workflow mode.\n+- The path repair rule is directionally correct: runtime-to-hub shared references keep hop-count and delete the old sibling segment; workflow-to-runtime references move one hop closer and target `runtime/`.\n+- Correction: `render-command-contract.cjs` has a `WORKSPACE_ROOT` constant that must gain one extra parent hop after nesting, just like `compile-command-contracts.cjs`.\n+- The `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow is load-bearing because it affects runtime typecheck and council test discovery.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n \n ---\n \n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n ## 6. WHAT WORKED\n-[None yet]\n+- Executable import and root-depth reads exposed one concrete correction that a prose-only rename inventory could miss (iteration 1).\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n \n ---\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n ## 7. WHAT FAILED\n-[None yet]\n+- Broad grep across all markdown was noisy; targeted reads of `.cjs`, `.ts`, `package.json`, and `vitest.config.ts` gave better signal (iteration 1).\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n \n ---\n \n@@ -60,9 +63,9 @@\n ---\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n ## 9. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n-[None yet]\n+- Add `runtime/` as an eighth workflow mode: ruled out because runtime is backend infrastructure and the public mode registry already models workflow modes separately (iteration 1, evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:19`).\n <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n \n ---\n \n@@ -74,9 +77,9 @@\n ---\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n-Iteration 1: Validate the proposed physical layout and internal path-coupling repair rules against the actual current files.\n+Iteration 2: Inventory external reference migration categories and stress-test whether child 003 covers executable, generated, advisor, agent, README, hook, CI, and graph surfaces without over-rewriting historical specs.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ---\n","additions":11,"deletions":8},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-findings-registry.json","relativePath":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-findings-registry.json","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n@@ -1,20 +1,44 @@\n {\n   \"openQuestions\": [\n-    \"Is the proposed system-deep-loop/runtime structural layout correct?\",\n-    \"Are forward and reverse path-coupling repair rules correct at concrete cal