{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487041245,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffe83jWKFM65pCjvi","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_GMdyRQhqjviir3EBKxIjCt3d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"deep-loop-workflows|deep-loop-runtime","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code","include":"*.{md,json,ts,js,cjs}"},"output":"Found 8 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/09--tooling-and-hooks/comment-hygiene-hook.md:\n  Line 130: **Where `deep-review` consumes it.** `deep-review` audits four dimensions — correctness, security, **traceability**, and maintainability (`.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/README.md:80`). The comment-hygiene envelope feeds the **traceability** dimension: a comment that still points at a spec path, packet/phase number, or ADR/REQ/task/finding id is exactly the kind of unstable, rot-prone reference the traceability pass is meant to catch, and the author-side envelope tells the reviewer which such references were already flagged, fixed, or deferred. `deep-review` then classifies each surviving finding by blocking severity — P0/P1/P2 (`.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/README.md:84`) — and those severity gates roll up into the release-readiness verdict, PASS / CONDITIONAL / FAIL (`.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/README.md:27`). A comment-hygiene deferral the author labelled low-risk typically lands as a P2 advisory that rides a PASS; one that obscures a real traceability defect can be escalated by the reviewer through its own adversarial re-read.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/quick_reference.md:\n  Line 61: - [review_mode_contract.yaml](../../../deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml) - Canonical review-mode contract manifest (source of truth for deep review taxonomy)\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/shared/references/smart_routing.md:\n  Line 301: A drift guard (`.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/tests/sk-code-router-sync.vitest.ts`) keeps this block honest: it fails if any path here is missing on disk, if any routable `references/`/`assets/` doc stops being covered, or if an explicit full path named in the prose maps is absent here. Run it standalone with `npx vitest run skill-benchmark/tests/sk-code-router-sync.vitest.ts` from `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts`.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/graph-metadata.json:\n  Line 31:         \"target\": \"deep-loop-workflows\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/benchmark/README.md:\n  Line 52: node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs \\\n\n  Line 62: node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs \\\n\n  Line 124: | [`deep-improvement`](../../deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/SKILL.md) | Owns the Lane C benchmark harness | Running or extending the benchmark |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/benchmark/d4r-live/README.md:\n  Line 30: node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs --skill sk-code --trace-mode live \\\n","metadata":{"matches":8,"truncated":false},"title":"deep-loop-workflows|deep-loop-runtime","time":{"start":1783487041224,"end":1783487041244}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08cce28d7538fc90016a4dda412bd881918ba5fa82a9f5eb60"}},"id":"prt_f401c8ec6001wAeNE21hQjFptV","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffe83jWKFM65pCjvi","messageID":"msg_f401c66d2001HImXawJiZv7cbK"}}
