{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487053174,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffe83jWKFM65pCjvi","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_Dcb2eD7c6VBLqb47ImPMkkWM","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"mk-deep-loop-guard|deep-loop-workflows|deep-loop-runtime","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode","include":"*mk-deep-loop-guard*"},"output":"Found 51 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/plugins/tests/mk-deep-loop-guard.test.cjs:\n  Line 2: // ║ COMPONENT: mk-deep-loop-guard Regression Tests                           ║\n\n  Line 25:   const registryDir = path.join(dir, '.opencode', 'skills', 'deep-loop-workflows');\n\n  Line 62:   const pluginUrl = pathToFileURL(path.join(__dirname, '..', 'mk-deep-loop-guard.js')).href;\n\n  Line 71:   const tmpDir = fs.mkdtempSync(path.join(os.tmpdir(), 'mk-deep-loop-guard-'));\n\n  Line 94:   assert.match(readGuardLog(tmpDir), /mk-deep-loop-guard.*mode mismatch/i);\n\n  Line 100:     /mk-deep-loop-guard: Deep Route mode mismatch/,\n\n  Line 105:   fs.rmSync(path.join(tmpDir, '.opencode', 'skills', 'deep-loop-workflows', 'mode-registry.json'));\n\n  Line 167:     /mk-deep-loop-guard: loop-like repeated dispatch/,\n\n  Line 274:   console.log('mk-deep-loop-guard.test.cjs: all assertions passed');\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js:\n  Line 2: // ║ COMPONENT: mk-deep-loop-guard OpenCode Plugin                            ║\n\n  Line 35: const REGISTRY_RELATIVE_PATH = '.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json';\n\n  Line 96:     'mk-deep-loop-guard: Deep Route mode mismatch --',\n\n  Line 205:     'mk-deep-loop-guard: loop-like repeated dispatch --',\n\n  Line 222:     const line = `${new Date().toISOString()} [mk-deep-loop-guard] WARN: ${detail}\\n`;\n\n  Line 344:  * Create the mk-deep-loop-guard OpenCode plugin hooks.\n\n  Line 413:         if (err instanceof Error && err.message.startsWith('mk-deep-loop-guard:')) throw err;\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/03--validation/mk-deep-loop-guard.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"DLR-052 -- mk-deep-loop-guard\"\n\n  Line 3: description: \"Manual validation scenario for mk-deep-loop-guard in the deep-loop-runtime skill.\"\n\n  Line 7: # DLR-052 -- mk-deep-loop-guard\n\n  Line 25: - Objective: Confirm mk-deep-loop-guard fires on a real Task dispatch, respects the warn/reject toggle for both checks, resolves identity correctly under `subagent_type=\"general\"`, fails open on registry/state errors, and ignores non-deep-mode and non-loop-executor dispatches.\n\n  Line 27: - Real user request: `Verify mk-deep-loop-guard still detects a Deep Route mode mismatch and a loop-like repeated dispatch, and respects MK_DEEP_LOOP_GUARD_REJECT / MK_DEEP_LOOP_GUARD_REJECT_LOOP.`\n\n  Line 39: - Feature catalog entry exists at `feature_catalog/03--validation/mk-deep-loop-guard.md`.\n\n  Line 43: 1. Run the automated regression test: `node .opencode/plugins/tests/mk-deep-loop-guard.test.cjs` and require EXIT 0 (covers identity resolution, loop-repeat thresholds, command-driven exemption, non-loop-executor exemption, cross-session isolation, and both fail-open paths hermetically).\n\n  Line 44: 2. Live warn-mode check: dispatch a Task call with a prompt containing `Agent: @ai-council` (or a direct `subagent_type=ai-council`) and `mode=research` via `opencode run --agent general \"...\"`; confirm a `[mk-deep-loop-guard] WARN: ... mode mismatch ...` line is appended to `.opencode/skills/.loop-guard-state/guard-warnings.log` (not printed to the console/TUI) and the dispatch still completes.\n\n  Line 75: | `.opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js` | OpenCode plugin entrypoint; registers and implements the `tool.execute.before` hook. |\n\n  Line 81: | `.opencode/plugins/tests/mk-deep-loop-guard.test.cjs` | Hermetic regression coverage for export shape, identity resolution, warn/reject toggles (mode-mismatch and loop-repeat), command-driven/non-loop-executor exemptions, cross-session isolation, and both fail-open paths. |\n\n  Line 89: - Feature catalog entry: `feature_catalog/03--validation/mk-deep-loop-guard.md`\n\n  Line 90: - Scenario file path: `manual_testing_playbook/03--validation/mk-deep-loop-guard.md`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/03--validation/mk-deep-loop-guard.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"mk-deep-loop-guard\"\n\n  Line 5:   - \"mk-deep-loop-guard\"\n\n  Line 15: # mk-deep-loop-guard (tool.execute.before plugin)\n\n  Line 25: This feature belongs to the validation group and is catalogued as F050 in the `deep-loop-runtime` inventory. It complements `post-dispatch-validate.ts` (F005) from the opposite direction: that validator inspects the JSONL record a dispatch already produced; this plugin inspects the dispatch args *before* the call executes.\n\n  Line 45: Default behavior for both checks is mutate-and-warn: on a mismatch or loop-repeat, the plugin appends a `[mk-deep-loop-guard] WARN: ...` line to `.opencode/skills/.loop-guard-state/guard-warnings.log` (never to stdout/stderr, which OpenCode's TUI paints onto the prompt input line during `tool.execute.before`) and lets the dispatch proceed. `MK_DEEP_LOOP_GUARD_REJECT=1` switches Check 1 to fail-closed; `MK_DEEP_LOOP_GUARD_REJECT_LOOP=1` independently switches Check 2 to fail-closed. Both throw-blocks-dispatch mechanisms are confirmed via live testing against the installed OpenCode host — throwing from `tool.execute.before` genuinely prevents the underlying tool call from executing, not merely logging a warning.\n\n  Line 69: | `.opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js` | Script | OpenCode plugin entrypoint; registers the `tool.execute.before` hook; implements identity resolution and both checks. |\n\n  Line 75: | `.opencode/plugins/tests/mk-deep-loop-guard.test.cjs` | Automated test | Hermetic regression coverage for export shape, identity resolution, both warn/reject toggles, command-driven/non-loop-executor exemptions, cross-session isolation, and both fail-open paths, run against a fixture registry (no live OpenCode session required). |\n\n  Line 86: - Feature file path: `03--validation/mk-deep-loop-guard.md`\n\n  Line 87: - Primary sources: `.opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js`, `.opencode/plugins/tests/mk-deep-loop-guard.test.cjs`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/031-deep-loop-gpt-reliability/changelog/003-guard-and-enforcement/changelog-003-005-mk-deep-loop-guard-retention.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"Changelog: mk-deep-loop-guard Retention [031-deep-loop-gpt-reliability/003-guard-and-enforcement/005-mk-deep-loop-guard-retention]\"\n\n  Line 3: description: \"Chronological changelog for the mk-deep-loop-guard retention phase moved in from packet 037.\"\n\n  Line 6:   - \"mk-deep-loop-guard retention changelog\"\n\n  Line 17: > Spec folder: `.opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-gpt-reliability/003-guard-and-enforcement/005-mk-deep-loop-guard-retention` (Level 1)\n\n  Line 22: Added age-based retention to `mk-deep-loop-guard.js`'s `.loop-guard-state` directory. The plugin now sweeps stale per-session JSON state, archives it, prunes old archives, and rotates `guard-warnings.log` when dormant, mirroring the `mk-goal.js` pattern while preserving the guard's synchronous I/O model.\n\n  Line 33: - `mk-deep-loop-guard.js` now owns cleanup for its state directory instead of leaving session files and warning logs unbounded.\n\n  Line 53: | `.opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js` | Modified | Added sweep/archive/prune functions, event hook, retention constants and warning-log rotation |\n\n  Line 54: | `.opencode/plugins/tests/mk-deep-loop-guard.test.cjs` | Modified | Added mutation-proved retention coverage |\n\n  Line 56: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/03--validation/mk-deep-loop-guard.md` | Modified | Added retention behavior |\n\n  Line 57: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/03--validation/mk-deep-loop-guard.md` | Modified | Added retention test step |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/031-deep-loop-gpt-reliability/changelog/003-guard-and-enforcement/changelog-003-002-mk-deep-loop-guard-hardening.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"Changelog: mk-deep-loop-guard Hardening Research [031-deep-loop-gpt-reliability/003-guard-and-enforcement/002-mk-deep-loop-guard-hardening]\"\n\n  Line 3: description: \"Chronological changelog for the mk-deep-loop-guard Hardening Research phase.\"\n\n  Line 17: > Spec folder: `.opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-gpt-reliability/003-guard-and-enforcement/002-mk-deep-loop-guard-hardening` (Level 1, research)\n\n  Line 22: 5-iteration dual-model research (`gpt-fast-high` 3 iterations + `glm-max` 2 iterations) on hardening `mk-deep-loop-guard.js` to mechanically detect loop-like repeated `orchestrate`-to-loop-executor dispatches. Both lineages independently converged on session-scoped state plus an iteration-aware heuristic, and surfaced a load-bearing fact: `orchestrate`'s Task dispatches always set `subagent_type: \"general\"`, meaning phase 011's existing mode-mismatch guard silently no-oped on real `orchestrate`-routed dispatches (flagged, implemented in phase 017).\n","metadata":{"matches":51,"truncated":false},"title":"mk-deep-loop-guard|deep-loop-workflows|deep-loop-runtime","time":{"start":1783487052897,"end":1783487053171}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_093a6aa074deba47016a4dda4cc8bc81919e5c2a4b2c4f12f1"}},"id":"prt_f401cbc45001aaqMntYFFRysSO","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffe83jWKFM65pCjvi","messageID":"msg_f401c925f001S6fjQGw0Q4nwID"}}
