gs\": 5,\n-    \"convergenceScore\": 0.8,\n+    \"iterationsCompleted\": 3,\n+    \"openQuestions\": 0,\n+    \"resolvedQuestions\": 5,\n+    \"keyFindings\": 8,\n+    \"convergenceScore\": 0.9,\n*** Update File: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-dashboard.md\n@@\n |---:|---|---:|---:|---|\n | 1 | Structural layout and bidirectional path-coupling repair | 0.86 | 5 | complete |\n | 2 | External reference migration coverage | 0.72 | 7 | complete |\n+| 3 | Fallback-router wiring scope | 0.44 | 7 | complete |\n \n ## Question Status\n-4/5 answered. Remaining: fallback-router wiring recommendation.\n+5/5 answered. Remaining: synthesis-readiness convergence pass.\n \n ## Convergence Trend\n-0.86 -> 0.72 (still high novelty; continue, minimum iteration floor not met).\n+0.86 -> 0.72 -> 0.44 (novelty declining; minimum iteration floor met, but run one convergence pass before synthesis).\n@@\n | Add `runtime/` as a workflow mode | Runtime is backend infrastructure; workflow modes are separately modeled in `mode-registry.json`. | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:19` | 1 |\n | Blind repo-wide find/replace | Generated contracts, advisor fields, graph edges, and historical eval fixtures need different handling. | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/data/ground-truth.json:795` | 2 |\n+| Mandatory child 004 in structural merge | Fallback wiring is behavior expansion requiring registry/schema, approval, model-id normalization, and attribution changes. | `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:42` | 3 |\n \n ## Next Focus\n-Evaluate fallback-router wiring and current fanout retry behavior.\n+Synthesis-readiness convergence pass, then final synthesis if no contradictions appear.\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/prompts/iteration-003.md\nA .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/iterations/iteration-003.md\nA .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deltas/iter-003.jsonl\nM .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-state.jsonl\nM .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-strategy.md\nM .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-findings-registry.json\nM .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-dashboard.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/prompts/iteration-003.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/prompts/iteration-003.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/prompts/iteration-003.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,17 @@\n+STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n+Segment: 1 | Iteration: 3 of 10\n+Questions: 4/5 answered | Last focus: External reference migration coverage\n+Last 2 ratios: 0.86 -> 0.72 | Stuck count: 0\n+Resource map: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.\n+Memory context refresh: none loaded yet.\n+Next focus: Evaluate fallback-router.ts, current fanout retry behavior, and whether GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback should be wired now or deferred.\n+\n+Research Topic: Validate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop.\n+Focus Area: Fallback-router wiring scope, current caller gap, fanout retry behavior, model registry state, and implementation risk.\n+State Files:\n+- Config: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-config.json\n+- State: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-state.jsonl\n+- Strategy: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n+- Output: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/iterations/iteration-003.md\n+\n+CONSTRAINT: LEAF research iteration; do not dispatch sub-agents and do not write outside the lineage artifact directory.\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/iterations/iteration-003.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/iterations/iteration-003.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/iterations/iteration-003.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,46 @@\n+# Iteration 3: Fallback-Router Wiring Scope\n+\n+## Focus\n+Determine whether the existing `fallback-router.ts` should be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, or deferred as optional behavior outside the structural unification packet.\n+\n+## Findings\n+\n+1. The fallback router is a shipped pure decision primitive, but it is not wired into runtime dispatch. The module exports `validateFallbackGraph`, `createFallbackRouter`, and `resolveFallback` [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:299] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:320] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:357]. A current code search found production references only in the module itself; callers are test-only (`fallback-router.vitest.ts` and `executor-provenance-mismatch.vitest.ts`) [SOURCE: grep resolveFallback/createFallbackRouter 2026-07-08T05:08Z] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/executor-provenance-mismatch.vitest.ts:237]. Child 004 correctly identifies the zero-production-caller gap.\n+\n+2. Current fanout behavior is same-lineage retry, not model fallback. `runCappedPool()` normalizes `maxRetries` and per-label retry counts [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:433] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:434], then requeues the same item/index/label while `result.error.retryable === true && retryCount < maxRetries` [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:628] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:633]. On exhaustion it sets `retry_exhausted` and records terminal failure [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:650] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:651]. Tests assert exactly that a timeout runs three attempts for `maxRetries: 2` and ends rejected with `retry_exhausted: true` [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fanout-pool.vitest.ts:557] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fanout-pool.vitest.ts:573].\n+\n+3. Child 004's core implementation target is too narrow. The plan says to add one call in `fanout-pool.cjs`'s retry-exhausted branch [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/plan.md:43] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/plan.md:90]. But `fanout-run.cjs` owns the model-bearing lineage object, lineage directory, session id, prompt, command construction, sandbox, dispatch env, and artifact validation [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1534] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1548] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1580] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1599]. A safe implementation needs `fanout-run.cjs` to participate, or `fanout-pool.cjs` needs a new typed callback contract that can create a replacement lineage while preserving pool accounting. This is more than a small local edit.\n+\n+4. The GLM-to-MiMo edge is not currently configured in the model registry data. `sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json` lists MiMo under `xiaomi-token-plan` with `fallback_target: null` [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:190] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:203] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:204]. It lists GLM-5.2 under `zai-coding-plan`, also with `fallback_target: null` [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:255] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:268] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:269]. The proposed child 004 registry entry is therefore new policy/configuration, not merely consuming existing data.\n+\n+5. Model-id normalization is a hidden requirement. The router uses profile ids such as `glm-5.2` and `mimo-v2.5-pro`, while fanout executor commands commonly carry provider slugs such as `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` and `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro` from the model profile capability fields [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:207] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:272]. `buildLineageCommand()` passes `lineage.model` directly to `opencode run --model` [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1343] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1349]. A fallback integration needs an explicit mapping between canonical fallback ids and executable provider slugs, or it risks failing `resolveFallback()` lookup or dispatching the wrong CLI model string.\n+\n+6. The approval guard makes fallback opt-in by design. `resolveFallback()` can reject a configured target outside the caller-approved model set [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:411] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:415], and tests cover both approved and unapproved substitution [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/executor-provenance-mismatch.vitest.ts:244] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/executor-provenance-mismatch.vitest.ts:252]. If the fallback target is not already one of the fanout executors, a new config field or policy source must explicitly approve it. Auto-reading a global fallback edge would change behavior for callers that requested only GLM.\n+\n+7. The fallback lineage must be separately attributable. Child 004's requirement says a fallback replica must not be silently indistinguishable from the failed GLM replica [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:94] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:96]. Current retry accounting is keyed by label [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:631] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:783], and lineage directories are also keyed by label [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1553]. Reusing the failed label for MiMo would mix artifacts and retry counts; a safe implementation needs a replacement label and status event such as `fallback_scheduled`, plus parent/target metadata in summary output.\n+\n+## Recommendation\n+Defer child 004 from the structural system-deep-loop merge unless the operator explicitly expands scope to behavior changes. It is valuable hardening, but it is not required to prove the rename/nesting/reference-migration design. If implemented later, revise child 004 first so the scope includes: fallback registry/schema or model-profile projection, canonical-id to CLI-slug normalization, explicit caller approval, a `fanout-run.cjs`/pool callback integration point, a separate fallback label/artifact directory, and a forced-failure integration test.\n+\n+## Sources Consulted\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/executor-provenance-mismatch.vitest.ts`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`\n+- `.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json`\n+- `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/{spec.md,plan.md,tasks.md}`\n+\n+## Assessment\n+- newInfoRatio: 0.44\n+- Novelty justification: The zero-caller gap was known, but the iteration added concrete implementation blockers: wrong narrow call-site assumption, missing current edge in registry data, canonical-id vs provider-slug mapping, approval-guard policy, and fallback-label attribution requirements.\n+- Confidence: High that defer is the safest recommendation for the structural merge; medium on exact implementation shape because no code change was performed.\n+\n+## Reflection\n+- What worked: Reading both pure-router tests and fanout runtime call sites separated a simple library gap from the actual orchestration integration problem.\n+- What failed: Treating fallback wiring as a one-line retry-exhaustion hook underestimates label, artifact, approval, and model-id coupling.\n+- Ruled out: Wiring child 004 as mandatory merge work without a scope-expansion decision.\n+\n+## Recommended Next Focus\n+Run one final synthesis-readiness/convergence pass across the three answered areas and produce the final research synthesis if no new contradictions appear.\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deltas/iter-003.jsonl\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deltas/iter-003.jsonl\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deltas/iter-003.jsonl\n@@ -0,0 +1,1 @@\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":3,\"run\":3,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Fallback-router wiring scope\",\"findingsCount\":7,\"newInfoRatio\":0.44,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Confirmed the zero-caller gap and added implementation blockers: narrow call-site assumption, missing registry edge, canonical-id/provider-slug mapping, approval policy, and fallback-label attribution.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Should fallback-router.ts be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Fallback-router wiring should remain optional/deferred for the structural merge unless the operator explicitly expands scope to behavior changes.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"f013-fallback-zero-production-caller\",\"summary\":\"fallback-router.ts is a shipped pure decision primitive with test-only callers and no production dispatch integration.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:357\",\"grep resolveFallback/createFallbackRouter 2026-07-08T05:08Z\"]},{\"id\":\"f014-fanout-same-label-retry\",\"summary\":\"fanout-pool retries the same item/index/label until maxRetries and then sets retry_exhausted; no model-swap path exists.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:628\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:650\"]},{\"id\":\"f015-fallback-callsite-too-narrow\",\"summary\":\"Child 004's proposed fanout-pool-only call site is too narrow because fanout-run owns model-bearing lineages, prompt construction, command dispatch, and artifact validation.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/plan.md:90\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1534\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1599\"]},{\"id\":\"f016-glm-mimo-edge-not-configured\",\"summary\":\"The current model profile registry lists both GLM-5.2 and MiMo-V2.5-Pro with fallback_target null, so GLM-to-MiMo fallback would be new policy/configuration.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:204\",\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:269\"]},{\"id\":\"f017-model-id-normalization-needed\",\"summary\":\"Fallback router ids differ from executable provider slugs, so integration needs canonical-id to CLI-slug normalization.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:207\",\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:272\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1349\"]},{\"id\":\"f018-fallback-approval-required\",\"summary\":\"The fallback router's approved-model guard means substitution must be explicitly approved by config/policy, not silently inferred from a global edge.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:411\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/executor-provenance-mismatch.vitest.ts:252\"]},{\"id\":\"f019-fallback-label-attribution\",\"summary\":\"A fallback lineage needs a distinct label/artifact directory and status event to avoid mixing failed GLM retry state with MiMo replacement output.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1553\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:783\"]}],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Make child 004 mandatory inside the structural merge without an operator scope-expansion decision\",\"reason\":\"Fallback wiring is behavior expansion requiring registry/schema, caller approval, model-id normalization, and attribution changes; it is not required for the rename/nesting/reference migration.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:42\"}],\"recommendedNextFocus\":\"Run synthesis-readiness/convergence pass and produce final research synthesis if no contradictions appear.\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:09:54Z\",\"durationMs\":276000,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-3-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-state.jsonl\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-state.jsonl\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-state.jsonl\n@@ -1,4 +1,5 @@\n {\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"Validate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\",\"maxIterations\":10,\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":0.05,\"convergenceMode\":\"default\",\"stopPolicy\":\"convergence\",\"stuckThreshold\":3,\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":true},\"createdAt\":\"2026-07-08T04:58:44Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research\",\"artifactDir\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3\",\"executor\":{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"openai/gpt-5.5-fast\"},\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-3-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1,\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}\n {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"normalized_topic\":\"validate and stress test the merge design for folding deep loop runtime into deep loop workflows as system deep loop structural layout bidirectional path coupling repair the system spec kit tooling borrow reference migration across commands agents readmes advisor corpus and whether fallback router ts should be wired for real glm 5 2 to mimo v2 5 pro fallback\",\"specPath\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/.deep-research.lock\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T04:58:44Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-3-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":1,\"run\":1,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Structural layout and bidirectional path-coupling repair\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.86,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Mostly confirmed the candidate layout and path rules, while adding a concrete missed WORKSPACE_ROOT repair in render-command-contract.cjs.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Is the proposed system-deep-loop/runtime structural layout correct?\",\"Are forward and reverse path-coupling repair rules correct at concrete call sites?\",\"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped and sufficient?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"The runtime-as-infrastructure layout is correct and should not become a workflow mode.\",\"The asymmetric path rule is correct, with one added root-depth repair for render-command-contract.cjs.\",\"The system-spec-kit tooling-borrow is load-bearing and belongs in the structural phase.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"f001-runtime-not-mode\",\"summary\":\"system-deep-loop/runtime should remain infrastructure, not a workflow mode.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:12\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:19\"]},{\"id\":\"f002-forward-rule-mostly-correct\",\"summary\":\"Forward runtime-to-hub shared references keep hop-count and delete the old sibling segment.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs:8\"]},{\"id\":\"f003-render-root-depth-missed\",\"summary\":\"render-command-contract.cjs has a WORKSPACE_ROOT depth constant that must gain one more parent hop after nesting.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs:13\"]},{\"id\":\"f004-reverse-rule-confirmed\",\"summary\":\"Workflow packet code moves one hop closer to runtime and should target ../../runtime or ../../../runtime depending on nested depth.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:14\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs:122\"]},{\"id\":\"f005-tooling-borrow-load-bearing\",\"summary\":\"Runtime typecheck and system-spec-kit council test discovery both rely on deep-loop-runtime paths and must be repaired in the structural phase.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/package.json:10\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts:18\"]}],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Add runtime as a workflow mode\",\"reason\":\"The live registry treats runtime as backendKind/runtimeLoopType infrastructure, while user-facing modes remain research/review/council/improvement.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:19\"}],\"recommendedNextFocus\":\"Inventory external reference migration categories and stress-test child 003 coverage.\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:01:18Z\",\"durationMs\":377000,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-3-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":2,\"run\":2,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"External reference migration coverage\",\"findingsCount\":7,\"newInfoRatio\":0.72,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Confirmed most migration categories and added two refinements: fresh Stage-A baseline authority and explicit allowlisting for historical active eval fixtures.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Is external reference migration complete and safely staged across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, and graph metadata?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"External reference migration is broadly complete and safely staged if Stage A is treated as authoritative and historical eval fixtures are reviewed or allowlisted instead of blindly renamed.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"f006-stage-a-live-baseline\",\"summary\":\"Live old-name inventory differs from the spec count; Stage A must capture the authoritative baseline immediately before edits.\",\"sources\":[\"command: rg-count sweep 2026-07-08T05:02Z\"]},{\"id\":\"f007-compiled-contracts-regenerate-only\",\"summary\":\"Compiled /deep command contracts embed generated headers, source digests, and old paths, so they must be regenerated rather than hand-edited.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_research.contract.md:1\",\".opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_research.contract.md:6\"]},{\"id\":\"f008-advisor-field-scope\",\"summary\":\"Advisor constants and routing fixtures require field-scoped migration plus accuracy re-baseline.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:83\",\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:109\"]},{\"id\":\"f009-plugin-fixture-pair\",\"summary\":\"mk-deep-loop-guard's registry path and test fixture must update together.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js:35\",\".opencode/plugins/tests/mk-deep-loop-guard.test.cjs:25\"]},{\"id\":\"f010-agent-duplicate-trees\",\"summary\":\"Both .opencode and .claude agent trees carry real old references and must be edited in lockstep.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/agents/orchestrate.md:185\",\".claude/agents/orchestrate.md:174\"]},{\"id\":\"f011-eval-fixture-allowlist\",\"summary\":\"Active system-spec-kit eval fixtures intentionally contain historical old-name queries/decoys and should be reviewed or allowlisted, not blindly renamed.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/data/ground-truth.json:795\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/data/ground-truth.json:960\"]},{\"id\":\"f012-graph-edge-collapse\",\"summary\":\"Sibling graph metadata needs edge collapse from two old identities to one system-deep-loop identity.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/graph-metadata.json:35\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/graph-metadata.json:40\"]}],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Blind repo-wide find/replace of old skill names\",\"reason\":\"Generated contracts, advisor fields, graph edges, and historical eval fixtures need different handling.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/data/ground-truth.json:795\"}],\"recommendedNextFocus\":\"Evaluate fallback-router.ts and current fanout retry behavior.\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:05:18Z\",\"durationMs\":520000,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-3-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":3,\"run\":3,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Fallback-router wiring scope\",\"findingsCount\":7,\"newInfoRatio\":0.44,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Confirmed the zero-caller gap and added implementation blockers: narrow call-site assumption, missing registry edge, canonical-id/provider-slug mapping, approval policy, and fallback-label attribution.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Should fallback-router.ts be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Fallback-router wiring should remain optional/deferred for the structural merge unless the operator explicitly expands scope to behavior changes.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"f013-fallback-zero-production-caller\",\"summary\":\"fallback-router.ts is a shipped pure decision primitive with test-only callers and no production dispatch integration.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:357\",\"grep resolveFallback/createFallbackRouter 2026-07-08T05:08Z\"]},{\"id\":\"f014-fanout-same-label-retry\",\"summary\":\"fanout-pool retries the same item/index/label until maxRetries and then sets retry_exhausted; no model-swap path exists.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:628\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:650\"]},{\"id\":\"f015-fallback-callsite-too-narrow\",\"summary\":\"Child 004's proposed fanout-pool-only call site is too narrow because fanout-run owns model-bearing lineages, prompt construction, command dispatch, and artifact validation.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/plan.md:90\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1534\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1599\"]},{\"id\":\"f016-glm-mimo-edge-not-configured\",\"summary\":\"The current model profile registry lists both GLM-5.2 and MiMo-V2.5-Pro with fallback_target null, so GLM-to-MiMo fallback would be new policy/configuration.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:204\",\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:269\"]},{\"id\":\"f017-model-id-normalization-needed\",\"summary\":\"Fallback router ids differ from executable provider slugs, so integration needs canonical-id to CLI-slug normalization.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:207\",\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:272\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1349\"]},{\"id\":\"f018-fallback-approval-required\",\"summary\":\"The fallback router's approved-model guard means substitution must be explicitly approved by config/policy, not silently inferred from a global edge.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:411\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/executor-provenance-mismatch.vitest.ts:252\"]},{\"id\":\"f019-fallback-label-attribution\",\"summary\":\"A fallback lineage needs a distinct label/artifact directory and status event to avoid mixing failed GLM retry state with MiMo replacement output.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1553\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:783\"]}],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Make child 004 mandatory inside the structural merge without an operator scope-expansion decision\",\"reason\":\"Fallback wiring is behavior expansion requiring registry/schema, caller approval, model-id normalization, and attribution changes; it is not required for the rename/nesting/reference migration.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:42\"}],\"recommendedNextFocus\":\"Run synthesis-readiness/convergence pass and produce final research synthesis if no contradictions appear.\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:09:54Z\",\"durationMs\":276000,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-3-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -10,9 +10,9 @@\n - [x] Is the proposed `system-deep-loop/runtime/` structural layout correct, especially treating runtime as infrastructure rather than a workflow mode?\n - [x] Are the forward and reverse relative-path repair rules correct at concrete call sites, or do any file-depth classes break the plan?\n - [x] Is the `system-spec-kit` TypeScript tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped and sufficient, or does it create a silent test-coverage gap?\n - [x] Is the external reference migration complete and safely staged across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, and graph metadata?\n-- [ ] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, deferred, or rejected for scope/behavior reasons?\n+- [x] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, deferred, or rejected for scope/behavior reasons?\n <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n \n ---\n \n@@ -36,8 +36,9 @@\n - The path repair rule is directionally correct: runtime-to-hub shared references keep hop-count and delete the old sibling segment; workflow-to-runtime references move one hop closer and target `runtime/`.\n - Correction: `render-command-contract.cjs` has a `WORKSPACE_ROOT` constant that must gain one extra parent hop after nesting, just like `compile-command-contracts.cjs`.\n - The `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow is load-bearing because it affects runtime typecheck and council test discovery.\n - External reference migration is broadly complete and safely staged, provided Stage A is rerun live and historical active eval fixtures are reviewed or allowlisted instead of blindly renamed.\n+- Fallback-router wiring should remain optional/deferred for the structural merge unless the operator explicitly expands scope to behavior changes.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n \n ---\n \n@@ -45,16 +46,18 @@\n <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n ## 6. WHAT WORKED\n - Executable import and root-depth reads exposed one concrete correction that a prose-only rename inventory could miss (iteration 1).\n - Category-splitting external references exposed generated-contract, advisor-corpus, plugin-fixture, agent-duplicate, and graph-edge handling differences (iteration 2).\n+- Reading fanout runtime call sites showed fallback wiring is a broader orchestration integration problem, not only a pure-router call (iteration 3).\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n \n ---\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n ## 7. WHAT FAILED\n - Broad grep across all markdown was noisy; targeted reads of `.cjs`, `.ts`, `package.json`, and `vitest.config.ts` gave better signal (iteration 1).\n - Treating all non-spec old-name hits as required rewrites is unsafe; active eval fixtures may intentionally preserve historical old-name queries (iteration 2).\n+- Treating child 004 as a one-line pool hook misses model-id normalization, approval, replacement label, and artifact-directory coupling (iteration 3).\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n \n ---\n \n@@ -68,8 +71,9 @@\n <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n ## 9. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n - Add `runtime/` as an eighth workflow mode: ruled out because runtime is backend infrastructure and the public mode registry already models workflow modes separately (iteration 1, evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:19`).\n - Blind repo-wide find/replace of old skill names: ruled out because generated contracts, advisor fields, graph edges, and historical eval fixtures need different handling (iteration 2, evidence: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/data/ground-truth.json:795`).\n+- Make child 004 mandatory inside the structural merge without operator scope expansion: ruled out because it is behavior expansion requiring registry/schema, caller approval, model-id normalization, and attribution changes (iteration 3, evidence: `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:42`).\n <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n \n ---\n \n@@ -81,9 +85,9 @@\n ---\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n-Iteration 3: Evaluate `fallback-router.ts`, its tests, current fanout retry behavior, and whether GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback should be wired in this packet or deferred.\n+Iteration 4: Run a synthesis-readiness/convergence pass across the answered structural, reference-migration, and fallback-scope findings; synthesize if no new contradictions appear.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ---\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n@@ -1,13 +1,12 @@\n {\n-  \"openQuestions\": [\n-    \"Should fallback-router.ts be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback?\"\n-  ],\n+  \"openQuestions\": [],\n   \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n     \"The system-deep-loop/runtime structural layout is correct and runtime should stay infrastructure, not a workflow mode.\",\n     \"The bidirectional path-coupling repair rule is correct, with a new correction for render-command-contract.cjs WORKSPACE_ROOT depth.\",\n     \"The system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair is load-bearing and correctly scoped to child 002.\",\n-    \"External reference migration is broadly complete if Stage A is live and historical active eval fixtures are allowlisted or reviewed.\"\n+    \"External reference migration is broadly complete if Stage A is live and historical active eval fixtures are allowlisted or reviewed.\",\n+    \"Fallback-router wiring should remain optional/deferred for the structural merge unless the operator explicitly expands scope to behavior changes.\"\n   ],\n   \"keyFindings\": [\n     {\n       \"id\": \"f001-runtime-not-mode\",\n@@ -32,8 +31,23 @@\n     {\n       \"id\": \"f012-graph-edge-collapse\",\n       \"summary\": \"Sibling graph metadata needs edge collapse from two old identities to one system-deep-loop identity.\",\n       \"sources\": [\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/graph-metadata.json:35\", \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/graph-metadata.json:40\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"f015-fallback-callsite-too-narrow\",\n+      \"summary\": \"Child 004's proposed fanout-pool-only call site is too narrow because fanout-run owns model-bearing lineages, prompt construction, command dispatch, and artifact validation.\",\n+      \"sources\": [\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/plan.md:90\", \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1534\", \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1599\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"f016-glm-mimo-edge-not-configured\",\n+      \"summary\": \"The current model profile registry lists both GLM-5.2 and MiMo-V2.5-Pro with fallback_target null, so GLM-to-MiMo fallback would be new policy/configuration.\",\n+      \"sources\": [\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:204\", \".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:269\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"f019-fallback-label-attribution\",\n+      \"summary\": \"A fallback lineage needs a distinct label/artifact directory and status event to avoid mixing failed GLM retry state with MiMo replacement output.\",\n+      \"sources\": [\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1553\", \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:783\"]\n     }\n   ],\n   \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n     {\n@@ -46,15 +60,21 @@\n       \"approach\": \"Blind repo-wide find/replace of old skill names\",\n       \"reason\": \"Generated contracts, advisor fields, graph edges, and historical eval fixtures need different handling.\",\n       \"evidence\": \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/data/ground-truth.json:795\",\n       \"iterations\": [2]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"approach\": \"Make child 004 mandatory inside the structural merge without an operator scope-expansion decision\",\n+      \"reason\": \"Fallback wiring is behavior expansion requiring registry/schema, caller approval, model-id normalization, and attribution changes; it is not required for the rename/nesting/reference migration.\",\n+      \"evidence\": \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:42\",\n+      \"iterations\": [3]\n     }\n   ],\n   \"metrics\": {\n-    \"iterationsCompleted\": 2,\n-    \"openQuestions\": 1,\n-    \"resolvedQuestions\": 4,\n-    \"keyFindings\": 5,\n-    \"convergenceScore\": 0.8,\n+    \"iterationsCompleted\": 3,\n+    \"openQuestions\": 0,\n+    \"resolvedQuestions\": 5,\n+    \"keyFindings\": 8,\n+    \"convergenceScore\": 0.9,\n     \"coverageBySources\": {}\n   }\n }\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-dashboard.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-dashboard.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-dashboard.md\n@@ -4,19 +4,21 @@\n | run | focus | newInfoRatio | findings count | status |\n |---:|---|---:|---:|---|\n | 1 | Structural layout and bidirectional path-coupling repair | 0.86 | 5 | complete |\n | 2 | External reference migration coverage | 0.72 | 7 | complete |\n+| 3 | Fallback-router wiring scope | 0.44 | 7 | complete |\n \n ## Question Status\n-4/5 answered. Remaining: fallback-router wiring recommendation.\n+5/5 answered. Remaining: synthesis-readiness convergence pass.\n \n ## Convergence Trend\n-0.86 -> 0.72 (still high novelty; continue, minimum iteration floor not met).\n+0.86 -> 0.72 -> 0.44 (novelty declining; minimum iteration floor met, but run one convergence pass before synthesis).\n \n ## Dead Ends\n | Approach | Reason | Evidence | Iteration |\n |---|---|---|---:|\n | Add `runtime/` as a workflow mode | Runtime is backend infrastructure; workflow modes are separately modeled in `mode-registry.json`. | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:19` | 1 |\n | Blind repo-wide find/replace | Generated contracts, advisor fields, graph edges, and historical eval fixtures need different handling. | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/data/ground-truth.json:795` | 2 |\n+| Mandatory child 004 in structural merge | Fallback wiring is behavior expansion requiring registry/schema, approval, model-id normalization, and attribution changes. | `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:42` | 3 |\n \n ## Next Focus\n-Evaluate fallback-router wiring and current fanout retry behavior.\n+Synthesis-readiness convergence pass, then final synthesis if no contradictions appear.\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/prompts/iteration-003.md","relativePath":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/prompts/iteration-003.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/prompts/iteration-003.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/prompts/iteration-003.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/prompts/iteration-003.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,17 @@\n+STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n+Segment: 1 | Iteration: 3 of 10\n+Questions: 4/5 answered | Last focus: External reference migration coverage\n+Last 2 ratios: 0.86 -> 0.72 | Stuck count: 0\n+Resource map: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.\n+Memory context refresh: none loaded yet.\n+Next focus: Evaluate fallback-router.ts, current fanout retry behavior, and whether GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback should be wired now or deferred.\n+\n+Research Topic: Validate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop.\n+Focus Area: Fallback-router wiring scope, current caller gap, fanout retry behavior, model registry state, and implementation risk.\n+State Files:\n+- Config: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-config.json\n+- State: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-state.jsonl\n+- Strategy: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n+- Output: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/iterations/iteration-003.md\n+\n+CONSTRAINT: LEAF research iteration; do not dispatch sub-agents and do not write outside the lineage artifact directory.\n","additions":17,"deletions":0},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/iterations/iteration-003.md","relativePath":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/iterations/iteration-003.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/iterations/iteration-003.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/iterations/iteration-003.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/iterations/iteration-003.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,46 @@\n+# Iteration 3: Fallback-Router Wiring Scope\n+\n+## Focus\n+Determine whether the existing `fallback-router.ts` should be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, or deferred as optional behavior outside the structural unification packet.\n+\n+## Findings\n+\n+1. The fallback router is a shipped pure decision primitive, but it is not wired into runtime dispatch. The module exports `validateFallbackGraph`, `createFallbackRouter`, and `resolveFallback` [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:299] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:320] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:357]. A current code search found production references only in the module itself; callers are test-only (`fallback-router.vitest.ts` and `executor-provenance-mismatch.vitest.ts`) [SOURCE: grep resolveFallback/createFallbackRouter 2026-07-08T05:08Z] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/executor-provenance-mismatch.vitest.ts:237]. Child 004 correctly identifies the zero-production-caller gap.\n+\n+2. Current fanout behavior is same-lineage retry, not model fallback. `runCappedPool()` normalizes `maxRetries` and per-label retry counts [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:433] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:434], then requeues the same item/index/label while `result.error.retryable === true && retryCount < maxRetries` [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:628] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:633]. On exhaustion it sets `retry_exhausted` and records terminal failure [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:650] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:651]. Tests assert exactly that a timeout runs three attempts for `maxRetries: 2` and ends rejected with `retry_exhausted: true` [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fanout-pool.vitest.ts:557] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fanout-pool.vitest.ts:573].\n+\n+3. Child 004's core implementation target is too narrow. The plan says to add one call in `fanout-pool.cjs`'s retry-exhausted branch [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/plan.md:43] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/plan.md:90]. But `fanout-run.cjs` owns the model-bearing lineage object, lineage directory, session id, prompt, command construction, sandbox, dispatch env, and artifact validation [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1534] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1548] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1580] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1599]. A safe implementation needs `fanout-run.cjs` to participate, or `fanout-pool.cjs` needs a new typed callback contract that can create a replacement lineage while preserving pool accounting. This is more than a small local edit.\n+\n+4. The GLM-to-MiMo edge is not currently configured in the model registry data. `sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json` lists MiMo under `xiaomi-token-plan` with `fallback_target: null` [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:190] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:203] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:204]. It lists GLM-5.2 under `zai-coding-plan`, also with `fallback_target: null` [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:255] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:268] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:269]. The proposed child 004 registry entry is therefore new policy/configuration, not merely consuming existing data.\n+\n+5. Model-id normalization is a hidden requirement. The router uses profile ids such as `glm-5.2` and `mimo-v2.5-pro`, while fanout executor commands commonly carry provider slugs such as `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` and `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro` from the model profile capability fields [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:207] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:272]. `buildLineageCommand()` passes `lineage.model` directly to `opencode run --model` [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1343] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1349]. A fallback integration needs an explicit mapping between canonical fallback ids and executable provider slugs, or it risks failing `resolveFallback()` lookup or dispatching the wrong CLI model string.\n+\n+6. The approval guard makes fallback opt-in by design. `resolveFallback()` can reject a configured target outside the caller-approved model set [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:411] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:415], and tests cover both approved and unapproved substitution [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/executor-provenance-mismatch.vitest.ts:244] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/executor-provenance-mismatch.vitest.ts:252]. If the fallback target is not already one of the fanout executors, a new config field or policy source must explicitly approve it. Auto-reading a global fallback edge would change behavior for callers that requested only GLM.\n+\n+7. The fallback lineage must be separately attributable. Child 004's requirement says a fallback replica must not be silently indistinguishable from the failed GLM replica [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:94] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:96]. Current retry accounting is keyed by label [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:631] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:783], and lineage directories are also keyed by label [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1553]. Reusing the failed label for MiMo would mix artifacts and retry counts; a safe implementation needs a replacement label and status event such as `fallback_scheduled`, plus parent/target metadata in summary output.\n+\n+## Recommendation\n+Defer child 004 from the structural system-deep-loop merge unless the operator explicitly expands scope to behavior changes. It is valuable hardening, but it is not required to prove the rename/nesting/reference-migration design. If implemented later, revise child 004 first so the scope includes: fallback registry/schema or model-profile projection, canonical-id to CLI-slug normalization, explicit caller approval, a `fanout-run.cjs`/pool callback integration point, a separate fallback label/artifact directory, and a forced-failure integration test.\n+\n+## Sources Consulted\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/executor-provenance-mismatch.vitest.ts`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`\n+- `.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json`\n+- `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/{spec.md,plan.md,tasks.md}`\n+\n+## Assessment\n+- newInfoRatio: 0.44\n+- Novelty justification: The zero-caller gap was known, but the iteration added concrete implementation blockers: wrong narrow call-site assumption, missing current edge in registry data, canonical-id vs provider-slug mapping, approval-guard policy, and fallback-label attribution requirements.\n+- Confidence: High that defer is the safest recommendation for the structural merge; medium on exact implementation shape because no code change was performed.\n+\n+## Reflection\n+- What worked: Reading both pure-router tests and fanout runtime call sites separated a simple library gap from the actual orchestration integration problem.\n+- What failed: Treating fallback wiring as a one-line retry-exhaustion hook underestimates label, artifact, approval, and model-id coupling.\n+- Ruled out: Wiring child 004 as mandatory merge work without a scope-expansion decision.\n+\n+## Recommended Next Focus\n+Run one final synthesis-readiness/convergence pass across the three answered areas and produce the final research synthesis if no new contradictions appear.\n","additions":46,"deletions":0},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deltas/iter-003.jsonl","relativePath":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deltas/iter-003.jsonl","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deltas/iter-003.jsonl\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deltas/iter-003.jsonl\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deltas/iter-003.jsonl\n@@ -0,0 +1,1 @@\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":3,\"run\":3,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Fallback-router wiring scope\",\"findingsCount\":7,\"newInfoRatio\":0.44,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Confirmed the zero-caller gap and added implementation blockers: narrow call-site assumption, missing registry edge, canonical-id/provider-slug mapping, approval policy, and fallback-label attribution.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Should fallback-router.ts be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Fallback-router wiring should remain optional/deferred for the structural merge unless the operator explicitly expands scope to behavior changes.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"f013-fallback-zero-production-caller\",\"summary\":\"fallback-router.ts is a shipped pure decision primitive with test-only callers and no production dispatch integration.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:357\",\"grep resolveFallback/createFallbackRouter 2026-07-08T05:08Z\"]},{\"id\":\"f014-fanout-same-label-retry\",\"summary\":\"fanout-pool retries the same item/index/label until maxRetries and then sets retry_exhausted; no model-swap path exists.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:628\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:650\"]},{\"id\":\"f015-fallback-callsite-too-narrow\",\"summary\":\"Child 004's proposed fanout-pool-only call site is too narrow because fanout-run owns model-bearing lineages, prompt construction, command dispatch, and artifact validation.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/plan.md:90\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1534\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1599\"]},{\"id\":\"f016-glm-mimo-edge-not-configured\",\"summary\":\"The current model profile registry lists both GLM-5.2 and MiMo-V2.5-Pro with fallback_target null, so GLM-to-MiMo fallback would be new policy/configuration.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:204\",\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:269\"]},{\"id\":\"f017-model-id-normalization-needed\",\"summary\":\"Fallback router ids differ from executable provider slugs, so integration needs canonical-id to CLI-slug normalization.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:207\",\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:272\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1349\"]},{\"id\":\"f018-fallback-approval-required\",\"summary\":\"The fallback router's approved-model guard means substitution must be explicitly approved by config/policy, not silently inferred from a global edge.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:411\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/executor-provenance-mismatch.vitest.ts:252\"]},{\"id\":\"f019-fallback-label-attribution\",\"summary\":\"A fallback lineage needs a distinct label/artifact directory and status event to avoid mixing failed GLM retry state with MiMo replacement output.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1553\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:783\"]}],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Make child 004 mandatory inside the structural merge without an operator scope-expansion decision\",\"reason\":\"Fallback wiring is behavior expansion requiring registry/schema, caller approval, model-id normalization, and attribution changes; it is not required for the rename/nesting/reference migration.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:42\"}],\"recommendedNextFocus\":\"Run synthesis-readiness/convergence pass and produce final research synthesis if no contradictions appear.\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:09:54Z\",\"durationMs\":276000,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-3-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n","additions":1,"deletions":0},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-state.jsonl","relativePath":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-state.jsonl","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-state.jsonl\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-state.jsonl\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-state.jsonl\n@@ -1,4 +1,5 @@\n {\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"Validate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\",\"maxIterations\":10,\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":0.05,\"convergenceMode\":\"default\",\"stopPolicy\":\"convergence\",\"stuckThreshold\":3,\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":true},\"createdAt\":\"2026-07-08T04:58:44Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research\",\"artifactDir\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3\",\"executor\":{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"openai/gpt-5.5-fast\"},\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-3-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1,\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}\n {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"normalized_topic\":\"validate and stress test the merge design for folding deep loop runtime into deep loop workflows as system deep loop structural layout bidirectional path coupling repair the system spec kit tooling borrow reference migration across commands agents readmes advisor corpus and whether fallback router ts should be wired for real glm 5 2 to mimo v2 5 pro fallback\",\"specPath\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/.deep-research.lock\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T04:58:44Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-3-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":1,\"run\":1,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Structural layout and bidirectional path-coupling repair\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.86,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Mostly confirmed the candidate layout and path rules, while adding a concrete missed WORKSPACE_ROOT repair in render-command-contract.cjs.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Is the proposed system-deep-loop/runtime structural layout correct?\",\"Are forward and reverse path-coupling repair rules correct at concrete call sites?\",\"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped and sufficient?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"The runtime-as-infrastructure layout is correct and should not become a workflow mode.\",\"The asymmetric path rule is correct, with one added root-depth repair for render-command-contract.cjs.\",\"The system-spec-kit tooling-borrow is load-bearing and belongs in the structural phase.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"f001-runtime-not-mode\",\"summary\":\"system-deep-loop/runtime should remain infrastructure, not a workflow mode.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:12\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:19\"]},{\"id\":\"f002-forward-rule-mostly-correct\",\"summary\":\"Forward runtime-to-hub shared references keep hop-count and delete the old sibling segment.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs:8\"]},{\"id\":\"f003-render-root-depth-missed\",\"summary\":\"render-command-contract.cjs has a WORKSPACE_ROOT depth constant that must gain one more parent hop after nesting.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs:13\"]},{\"id\":\"f004-reverse-rule-confirmed\",\"summary\":\"Workflow packet code moves one hop closer to runtime and should target ../../runtime or ../../../runtime depending on nested depth.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:14\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs:122\"]},{\"id\":\"f005-tooling-borrow-load-bearing\",\"summary\":\"Runtime typecheck and system-spec-kit council test discovery both rely on deep-loop-runtime paths and must be repaired in the structural phase.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/package.json:10\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts:18\"]}],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Add runtime as a workflow mode\",\"reason\":\"The live registry treats runtime as backendKind/runtimeLoopType infrastructure, while user-facing modes remain research/review/council/improvement.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:19\"}],\"recommendedNextFocus\":\"Inventory external reference migration categories and stress-test child 003 coverage.\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:01:18Z\",\"durationMs\":377000,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-3-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":2,\"run\":2,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"External reference migration coverage\",\"findingsCount\":7,\"newInfoRatio\":0.72,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Confirmed most migration categories and added two refinements: fresh Stage-A baseline authority and explicit allowlisting for historical active eval fixtures.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Is external reference migration complete and safely staged across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, and graph metadata?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"External reference migration is broadly complete and safely staged if Stage A is treated as authoritative and historical eval fixtures are reviewed or allowlisted instead of blindly renamed.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"f006-stage-a-live-baseline\",\"summary\":\"Live old-name inventory differs from the spec count; Stage A must capture the authoritative baseline immediately before edits.\",\"sources\":[\"command: rg-count sweep 2026-07-08T05:02Z\"]},{\"id\":\"f007-compiled-contracts-regenerate-only\",\"summary\":\"Compiled /deep command contracts embed generated headers, source digests, and old paths, so they must be regenerated rather than hand-edited.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_research.contract.md:1\",\".opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_research.contract.md:6\"]},{\"id\":\"f008-advisor-field-scope\",\"summary\":\"Advisor constants and routing fixtures require field-scoped migration plus accuracy re-baseline.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:83\",\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:109\"]},{\"id\":\"f009-plugin-fixture-pair\",\"summary\":\"mk-deep-loop-guard's registry path and test fixture must update together.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js:35\",\".opencode/plugins/tests/mk-deep-loop-guard.test.cjs:25\"]},{\"id\":\"f010-agent-duplicate-trees\",\"summary\":\"Both .opencode and .claude agent trees carry real old references and must be edited in lockstep.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/agents/orchestrate.md:185\",\".claude/agents/orchestrate.md:174\"]},{\"id\":\"f011-eval-fixture-allowlist\",\"summary\":\"Active system-spec-kit eval fixtures intentionally contain historical old-name queries/decoys and should be reviewed or allowlisted, not blindly renamed.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/data/ground-truth.json:795\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/data/ground-truth.json:960\"]},{\"id\":\"f012-graph-edge-collapse\",\"summary\":\"Sibling graph metadata needs edge collapse from two old identities to one system-deep-loop identity.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/graph-metadata.json:35\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/graph-metadata.json:40\"]}],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Blind repo-wide find/replace of old skill names\",\"reason\":\"Generated contracts, advisor fields, graph edges, and historical eval fixtures need different handling.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/data/ground-truth.json:795\"}],\"recommendedNextFocus\":\"Evaluate fallback-router.ts and current fanout retry behavior.\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:05:18Z\",\"durationMs\":520000,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-3-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":3,\"run\":3,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Fallback-router wiring scope\",\"findingsCount\":7,\"newInfoRatio\":0.44,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Confirmed the zero-caller gap and added implementation blockers: narrow call-site assumption, missing registry edge, canonical-id/provider-slug mapping, approval policy, and fallback-label attribution.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Should fallback-router.ts be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Fallback-router wiring should remain optional/deferred for the structural merge unless the operator explicitly expands scope to behavior changes.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"f013-fallback-zero-production-caller\",\"summary\":\"fallback-router.ts is a shipped pure decision primitive with test-only callers and no production dispatch integration.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:357\",\"grep resolveFallback/createFallbackRouter 2026-07-08T05:08Z\"]},{\"id\":\"f014-fanout-same-label-retry\",\"summary\":\"fanout-pool retries the same item/index/label until maxRetries and then sets retry_exhausted; no model-swap path exists.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:628\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:650\"]},{\"id\":\"f015-fallback-callsite-too-narrow\",\"summary\":\"Child 004's proposed fanout-pool-only call site is too narrow because fanout-run owns model-bearing lineages, prompt construction, command dispatch, and artifact validation.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/plan.md:90\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1534\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1599\"]},{\"id\":\"f016-glm-mimo-edge-not-configured\",\"summary\":\"The current model profile registry lists both GLM-5.2 and MiMo-V2.5-Pro with fallback_target null, so GLM-to-MiMo fallback would be new policy/configuration.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:204\",\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:269\"]},{\"id\":\"f017-model-id-normalization-needed\",\"summary\":\"Fallback router ids differ from executable provider slugs, so integration needs canonical-id to CLI-slug normalization.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:207\",\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:272\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1349\"]},{\"id\":\"f018-fallback-approval-required\",\"summary\":\"The fallback router's approved-model guard means substitution must be explicitly approved by config/policy, not silently inferred from a global edge.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:411\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/executor-provenance-mismatch.vitest.ts:252\"]},{\"id\":\"f019-fallback-label-attribution\",\"summary\":\"A fallback lineage needs a distinct label/artifact directory and status event to avoid mixing failed GLM retry state with MiMo replacement output.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1553\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:783\"]}],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Make child 004 mandatory inside the structural merge without an operator scope-expansion decision\",\"reason\":\"Fallback wiring is behavior expansion requiring registry/schema, caller approval, model-id normalization, and attribution changes; it is not required for the rename/nesting/reference migration.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:42\"}],\"recommendedNextFocus\":\"Run synthesis-readiness/convergence pass and produce final research synthesis if no contradictions appear.\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:09:54Z\",\"durationMs\":276000,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-3-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n","additions":1,"deletions":0},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-strategy.md","relativePath":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-strategy.md","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -10,9 +10,9 @@\n - [x] Is the proposed `system-deep-loop/runtime/` structural layout correct, especially treating runtime as infrastructure rather than a workflow mode?\n - [x] Are the forward and reverse relative-path repair rules correct at concrete call sites, or do any file-depth classes break the plan?\n - [x] Is the `system-spec-kit` TypeScript tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped and sufficient, or does it create a silent test-coverage gap?\n - [x] Is the external reference migration complete and safely staged across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, and graph metadata?\n-- [ ] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, deferred, or rejected for scope/behavior reasons?\n+- [x] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, deferred, or rejected for scope/behavior reasons?\n <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n \n ---\n \n@@ -36,8 +36,9 @@\n - The path repair rule is directionally correct: runtime-to-hub shared references keep hop-count and delete the old sibling segment; workflow-to-runtime references move one hop closer and target `runtime/`.\n - Correction: `render-command-contract.cjs` has a `WORKSPACE_ROOT` constant that must gain one extra parent hop after nesting, just like `compile-command-contracts.cjs`.\n - The `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow is load-bearing because it affects runtime typecheck and council test discovery.\n - External reference migration is broadly complete and safely staged, provided Stage A is rerun live and historical active eval fixtures are reviewed or allowlisted instead of blindly renamed.\n+- Fallback-router wiring should remain optional/deferred for the structural merge unless the operator explicitly expands scope to behavior changes.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n \n ---\n \n@@ -45,16 +46,18 @@\n <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n ## 6. WHAT WORKED\n - Executable import and root-depth reads exposed one concrete correction that a prose-only rename inventory could miss (iteration 1).\n - Category-splitting external references exposed generated-contract, advisor-corpus, plugin-fixture, agent-duplicate, and graph-edge handling differences (iteration 2).\n+- Reading fanout runtime call sites showed fallback wiring is a broader orchestration integration problem, not only a pure-router call (iteration 3).\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n \n ---\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n ## 7. WHAT FAILED\n - Broad grep across all markdown was noisy; targeted reads of `.cjs`, `.ts`, `package.json`, and `vitest.config.ts` gave better signal (iteration 1).\n - Treating all non-spec old-name hits as required rewrites is unsafe; active eval fixtures may intentionally preserve historical old-name queries (iteration 2).\n+- Treating child 004 as a one-line pool hook misses model-id normalization, approval, replacement label, and artifact-directory coupling (iteration 3).\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n \n ---\n \n@@ -68,8 +71,9 @@\n <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n ## 9. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n - Add `runtime/` as an eighth workflow mode: ruled out because runtime is backend infrastructure and the public mode registry already models workflow modes separately (iteration 1, evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:19`).\n - Blind repo-wide find/replace of old skill names: ruled out because generated contracts, advisor fields, graph edges, and historical eval fixtures need different handling (iteration 2, evidence: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/data/ground-truth.json:795`).\n+- Make child 004 mandatory inside the structural merge without operator scope expansion: ruled out because it is behavior expansion requiring registry/schema, caller approval, model-id normalization, and attribution changes (iteration 3, evidence: `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:42`).\n <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n \n ---\n \n@@ -81,9 +85,9 @@\n ---\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n-Iteration 3: Evaluate `fallback-router.ts`, its tests, current fanout retry behavior, and whether GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback should be wired in this packet or deferred.\n+Iteration 4: Run a synthesis-readiness/convergence pass across the answered structural, reference-migration, and fallback-scope findings; synthesize if no new contradictions appear.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ---\n","additions":6,"deletions":2},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-findings-registry.json","relativePath":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-findings-registry.json","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n@@ -1,13 +1,12 @@\n {\n-  \"openQuestions\": [\n-    \"Should fallback-router.ts be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback?\"\n-  ],\n+  \"openQuestions\": [],\n   \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n     \"The system-deep-loop/runtime structural layout is correct and runtime should stay infrastructure, not a workflow mode.\",\n     \"The bidirectional path-coupling repair rule is correct, with a new correction for render-command-contract.cjs WORKSPACE_ROOT depth.\",\n     \"The system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair is load-bearing and correctly scoped to child 002.\",\n-    \"External reference migration is broadly complete if Stage A is live and historical active eval fixtures are allowlisted or reviewed.\"\n+    \"External reference migration is broadly complete if Stage A is live and historical active eval fixtures are allowlisted or reviewed.\",\n+    \"Fallback-router wiring should remain optional/deferred fo