ep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/orchestrate-session.cjs:\n  Line 434: function sessionSynthesisFinding(sessionState, topicResults, stopReason) {\n\n  Line 441:     claim: `Session ${sessionState.session.session_id} completed ${topicResults.length} topic(s): ${stopReason}`,\n\n  Line 446:       stop_reason: stopReason,\n\n  Line 535:   let stopReason = 'topics_exhausted';\n\n  Line 545:       stopReason = 'max_topics_per_session';\n\n  Line 589:       stopReason = 'session_saturation_threshold';\n\n  Line 595:       stopReason = 'max_topics_per_session';\n\n  Line 601:   appendFinding(packetSpecFolder, sessionSynthesisFinding(sessionState, topicResults, stopReason));\n\n  Line 608:     stop_reason: stopReason,\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml:\n  Line 365:           - totalIterations\n\n  Line 371:           - stopReason\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md:\n  Line 91: Every terminal stop and every blocked-stop vote MUST emit the shared stop contract from REQ-001: a named `stopReason` enum plus, when STOP is vetoed, a `blocked_stop` event written to `deep-review-state.jsonl`. There is no nested `legalStop` wrapper on the persisted path. Earlier drafts of this document implied one, and that drift was the source of F009 in the 042 closing audit.\n\n  Line 93: #### stopReason Enum\n\n  Line 95: | `stopReason` | Meaning |\n\n  Line 153: 5. **Legal-stop gate bundle** -- review-specific stop gates. If a stop vote fails any gate, persist `stopReason=blockedStop` and continue.\n\n  Line 166:   return { action: \"STOP\", stopReason: \"maxIterationsReached\" }\n\n  Line 177:       return { action: \"STOP\", stopReason: \"converged\" }\n\n  Line 180: Triggers when all 4 dimensions (correctness, security, traceability, maintainability) are covered, no active P0/P1 remains, at least 1 stabilization pass has occurred, and the 5-gate legal-stop bundle passes. If gates fail, the loop records `stopReason=blockedStop` and continues despite full coverage.\n\n  Line 209: The recovery entry uses `stopReason=stuckRecovery` while the loop is in recovery. If recovery later terminates the run, the terminal record keeps the same shared enum value instead of minting a review-only label.\n\n  Line 499: | Legacy label | New `stopReason` | Mapping note |\n\n  Line 576: - `stopReason` enum values and semantics\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence_reference_only.md:\n  Line 91: - `stopReason` enum values and semantics;\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md:\n  Line 59: ### stopReason Values\n\n  Line 74: | Legacy label or phrase | New `stopReason` |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md:\n  Line 168: `synthesis_complete` events are authoritative for terminal status when present.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md:\n  Line 194:   \"stopReason\": \"blockedStop\",\n\n  Line 209:   \"stopReason\": \"userPaused\",\n\n  Line 223:   \"stopReason\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n\n  Line 323: Emission-time normalization maps legacy labels into canonical `stopReason` values before persistence. The mapping lives in `../convergence/convergence.md`.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md:\n  Line 187:    - Log event to JSONL: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":N,\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\",\"timestamp\":\"<ISO8601>\",\"sessionId\":\"<sid>\",\"generation\":G}`\n\n  Line 551: 6. **Final JSONL entry**: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"totalIterations\":N,\"answeredCount\":A,\"totalQuestions\":Q,\"stopReason\":\"converged\"}`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:\n  Line 1779:   const latestSynthesisComplete = eventRecords.filter((record) => record.event === 'synthesis_complete').at(-1);\n\n  Line 1794:     stopReason: typeof latestSynthesisComplete.stopReason === 'string' && latestSynthesisComplete.stopReason\n\n  Line 1795:       ? latestSynthesisComplete.stopReason\n\n  Line 1797:     totalIterations: isFiniteNumber(latestSynthesisComplete.totalIterations)\n\n  Line 1798:       ? latestSynthesisComplete.totalIterations\n\n  Line 2411:     ...(terminalStop?.stopReason ? [`- stopReason: ${terminalStop.stopReason}`] : []),\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/changelog/v1.6.2.0.md:\n  Line 14: The research reducer dropped `synthesis_complete` events and derived dashboard status from stale config. `reduce-state.cjs` now parses the latest `synthesis_complete` event to derive dashboard status.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:\n  Line 8: - `step_normalize_pause_events` rewrites raw `paused` to `userPaused` and raw `stuck_recovery` to `stuckRecovery` at emission time using the frozen `STOP_REASONS` enum. The live workflow no longer leaks free-form strings into `synthesis_complete.stopReason`.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:\n  Line 528: Prompt summary: As a manual-testing orchestrator, validate the graph stop-blocking guard contract for deep-research against the current deep-research docs, command entrypoint, YAML workflow, and runtime anchors. Verify SOURCE_DIVERSITY_THRESHOLD = 0.4 blocks STOP when unmet, and that the research convergence reference records blocked-stop persistence with stopReason: \"blockedStop\" when legal-stop gates fail. Return a concise operator-facing verdict.\n\n  Line 530: Expected signals: `SOURCE_DIVERSITY_THRESHOLD = 0.4`; `evaluateGraphGates()` fails `sourceDiversity` when below threshold; research convergence docs map failed legal-stop gates to `stopReason: \"blockedStop\"` and `blocked_stop` persistence.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence_recovery.md:\n  Line 169:   \"stopReason\": \"converged\",\n\n  Line 170:   \"totalIterations\": 5,\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_jsonl.md:\n  Line 178:   \"type\": \"event\", \"event\": \"synthesis_complete\", \"mode\": \"review\",\n\n  Line 179:   \"totalIterations\": 6, \"verdict\": \"PASS\",\n\n  Line 181:   \"dimensionCoverage\": 1.0, \"stopReason\": \"composite_converged\",\n\n  Line 186: **Required:** `type`, `event`, `mode`, `totalIterations`, `verdict`, `activeP0`, `activeP1`, `activeP2`, `dimensionCoverage`, `stopReason`, `timestamp`\n\n  Line 269:   \"stopReason\": \"userPaused\",\n\n  Line 282:   \"stopReason\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/changelog/v1.3.2.0.md:\n  Line 14: The reducer ignored `synthesis_complete` events and derived dashboard status from stale config, so the dashboard never showed the actual stop reason or legal-stop outcome after a loop finished. `reduce-state.cjs` now parses the latest `synthesis_complete` JSONL record and derives `stopReason` and terminal legal-stop bundle from it.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md:\n  Line 215:    - Log event to JSONL: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"reason\":\"sentinel file detected\"}`\n\n  Line 517:      \"event\": \"synthesis_complete\",\n\n  Line 519:      \"totalIterations\": N,\n\n  Line 525:      \"stopReason\": \"...\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/manual_testing_playbook/06--synthesis-save-and-guardrails/final-synthesis-memory-save-and-guardrail-behavior.md:\n  Line 48: 1. `bash: rg -n 'generate-context.js|synthesis_complete|research/research.md|memory' .opencode/commands/deep/research.md .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/README.md`\n\n  Line 50: 3. `bash: rg -n 'phase_synthesis|phase_save|generate-context.js|synthesis_complete|wave|segment|direct_mode' .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_confirm.yaml .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/quick_reference.md`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/assets/agent_improvement/improvement_charter.md:\n  Line 85: | Session end | `session_ended` | stopReason, sessionOutcome, finalIteration |\n\n  Line 89: - **stopReason** (WHY session ended): `converged`, `maxIterationsReached`, `blockedStop`, `manualStop`, `error`, `stuckRecovery`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/manual_testing_playbook/07--command-flow-stress-tests/pause-sentinel-halt.md:\n  Line 30: - Expected signals: `.deep-research-pause`, `userPaused`, `stopReason\":\"userPaused`, no `iteration-001.md`, config/state files, clean diffs.\n\n  Line 88: { grep -c '.deep-research-pause' /tmp/cp-049-B-combined.txt; grep -c 'userPaused' /tmp/cp-049-B-combined.txt; grep -c 'stopReason\":\"userPaused' /tmp/cp-049-B-combined.txt; test -s /tmp/cp-049-spec/research/deep-research-config.json && echo 1 || echo 0; test -s /tmp/cp-049-spec/research/deep-research-state.jsonl && echo 1 || echo 0; test ! -e /tmp/cp-049-spec/research/iterations/iteration-001.md && echo 1 || echo 0; grep -q 'POST_B_CANONICAL_DIFF=0' /tmp/cp-049-B-canonical-exit.txt && echo 1 || echo 0; grep -q 'TRIPWIRE_DIFF_EXIT=0' /tmp/cp-049-tripwire-exit.txt && echo 1 || echo 0; } | tee /tmp/cp-049-B-field-counts.txt\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/manual_testing_playbook/03--iteration-execution-and-state-discipline/progressive-synthesis-behavior-for-research-md.md:\n  Line 50: 3. `bash: rg -n 'phase_synthesis|research_output|synthesis_complete' .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_confirm.yaml`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/manual_testing_playbook/04--convergence-and-recovery/graph-convergence-signals.md:\n  Line 35: - Expected signals: `SOURCE_DIVERSITY_THRESHOLD = 0.4`; `evaluateGraphGates()` fails `sourceDiversity` when below threshold; research convergence docs map failed legal-stop gates to `stopReason: \"blockedStop\"` and `blocked_stop` persistence.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/manual_testing_playbook/06--synthesis-save-and-guardrails/final-synthesis-memory-save-and-guardrail-behavior.md:\n  Line 48: 1. `bash: rg -n 'generate-context.js|memory.*save|synthesis_complete|review-report|memory' .opencode/commands/deep/review.md .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/README.md`\n\n  Line 50: 3. `bash: rg -n 'phase_synthesis|phase_save|generate-context.js|synthesis_complete|memory_save|review-report' .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/feature_catalog/02--state-management/pause-sentinel.md:\n  Line 25: Before each dispatch, Step 2a checks for `review/.deep-review-pause` (the file name uses the shared `-pause` suffix). When the sentinel exists, the loop logs a JSONL event `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"reason\":\"sentinel file detected\"}` and halts with a message instructing the operator to delete the sentinel to resume. Resuming reads persisted state and continues from the last completed iteration rather than restarting from iteration 1.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/feature_catalog/02--state-management/jsonl-state-log.md:\n  Line 27: The same file also persists first-class lifecycle events such as `blocked_stop`, `graph_convergence`, `userPaused`, `stuckRecovery`, and `synthesis_complete`. Because the loop recomputes decisions from stored state, the JSONL contract is load-bearing for convergence replay, dashboard refreshes, and restart-safe reducer output.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/SKILL.md:\n  Line 333: Every improvement session termination MUST produce both a `stopReason` (why) and a `sessionOutcome` (what happened).\n\n  Line 335: **stopReason** (WHY the session ended):\n\n  Line 380: A session may NOT claim `converged` unless all five gate bundles pass: `contractGate`, `behaviorGate`, `integrationGate`, `evidenceGate`, and `improvementGate`. The orchestrator emits `legal_stop_evaluated` with nested `details.gateResults` before any `session_end`. Failures emit `blocked_stop` with `failedGates[]` and `stopReason:\"blockedStop\"`.\n\n  Line 470: Keep session-end emissions aligned to those helper-owned values until the helper contract itself changes. Labels such as `convergedImprovement`, `plateau`, `benchmarkPlateau`, `rejected`, `deferred`, `blocked`, or `errored` are not accepted by the current CLI validator. Plateau detection is a reducer/stop-rule condition. It must reconcile to one of the canonical stop reasons above when emitted as `details.stopReason`.\n\n  Line 494: - `improvement-journal.jsonl` to summarize last session boundaries, total replayed events, per-event counts, and terminal `stopReason` / `sessionOutcome`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:\n  Line 458: every completed improvement session emits a `session_ended` event with a valid `stopReason` and `sessionOutcome` drawn from the frozen taxonomies defined in `improvement-journal.cjs`.\n\n  Line 461: Prompt summary: As a manual-testing orchestrator, validate that every completed improvement session emits a session_ended event with a valid stopReason and sessionOutcome drawn from the frozen taxonomies defined in improvement-journal.cjs against the current deep-improvement command, runtime artifacts, and validation scripts. Verify Journal contains at least one `session_ended` or `session_end` event. Return a concise operator-facing PASS/FAIL verdict with the decisive evidence.\n\n  Line 463: Expected signals: Journal contains at least one `session_ended` or `session_end` event; `details.stopReason` is one of: `converged`, `maxIterationsReached`, `blockedStop`, `manualStop`, `error`, `stuckRecovery`; `details.sessionOutcome` is one of: `keptBaseline`, `promoted`, `rolledBack`, `advisoryOnly`; Both fields are present (validation rejects events missing either); `emitEvent()` refuses to write a `session_ended` event with an invalid stopReason or sessionOutcome\n\n  Line 650: Prompt summary: Dispatch the same insufficient-benchmark fixture task twice. Call B must emit `legal_stop_evaluated` with `contractGate`, `behaviorGate`, `integrationGate`, `evidenceGate`, and `improvementGate`, then `blocked_stop` with `failedGates` containing `evidenceGate`; no `stopReason\":\"converged\"` is allowed.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs:\n  Line 302:   let stopReason = null;\n\n  Line 322:       stopReason =\n\n  Line 323:         typeof details.stopReason === 'string' && details.stopReason.trim()\n\n  Line 324:           ? details.stopReason\n\n  Line 325:           : stopReason;\n\n  Line 353:     stopReason,\n\n  Line 1225: | Stop reason | ${formatDashboardValue(summary.stopReason)} |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md:\n  Line 16: - Added `scripts/improvement-journal.cjs` - append-only JSONL journal with event-type validation. Event types: `session_start`, `candidate_generated`, `scored`, `gate_evaluation`, `session_end`. `session_ended` requires `stopReason` and `sessionOutcome`.\n\n  Line 50: - Five P1 review findings from the ten-iteration deep-review pass were closed: CLI entrypoint, reducer rejection enum, required stopReason/sessionOutcome, scanner output mapping, scoreDynamic weights override.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/feature_catalog/01--loop-lifecycle/synthesis.md:\n  Line 29: Negative knowledge is part of the live contract here. Synthesis must consolidate `ruledOut` entries and `Dead Ends` sections into a required `Eliminated Alternatives` table. It also updates the config status to `complete` and appends a `synthesis_complete` event so later tooling can tell the packet has reached terminal synthesis.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/tests/fixtures/low-sample-benchmark/experiment-registry.json:\n  Line 175:     \"stopReason\": \"converged\",\n\n\n(Results truncated. Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":100,"truncated":true},"title":"synthesis_complete|research_complete|stopReason|totalIterations","time":{"start":1783487595920,"end":1783487595956}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_04daa1d4e6d9f42a016a4ddc6bca3c8191a07288916e064a30"}},"id":"prt_f40250584001LmfmWBVXrPZhUJ","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffe83jWKFM65pCjvi","messageID":"msg_f4024e6910016J2akzg1CZnjKY"}}
