p_server/lib/eval/data/ground-truth.json:795\", \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/data/ground-truth.json:960\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"f012-graph-edge-collapse\",\n      \"summary\": \"Sibling graph metadata needs edge collapse from two old identities to one system-deep-loop identity.\",\n      \"sources\": [\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/graph-metadata.json:35\", \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/graph-metadata.json:40\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"f015-fallback-callsite-too-narrow\",\n      \"summary\": \"Child 004's proposed fanout-pool-only call site is too narrow because fanout-run owns model-bearing lineages, prompt construction, command dispatch, and artifact validation.\",\n      \"sources\": [\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/plan.md:90\", \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1534\", \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1599\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"f016-glm-mimo-edge-not-configured\",\n      \"summary\": \"The current model profile registry lists both GLM-5.2 and MiMo-V2.5-Pro with fallback_target null, so GLM-to-MiMo fallback would be new policy/configuration.\",\n      \"sources\": [\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:204\", \".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:269\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"f019-fallback-label-attribution\",\n      \"summary\": \"A fallback lineage needs a distinct label/artifact directory and status event to avoid mixing failed GLM retry state with MiMo replacement output.\",\n      \"sources\": [\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1553\", \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:783\"]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n    {\n      \"approach\": \"Add runtime as a workflow mode\",\n      \"reason\": \"The live registry treats runtime as backend infrastructure.\",\n      \"evidence\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:19\",\n      \"iterations\": [1]\n    },\n    {\n      \"approach\": \"Blind repo-wide find/replace of old skill names\",\n      \"reason\": \"Generated contracts, advisor fields, graph edges, and historical eval fixtures need different handling.\",\n      \"evidence\": \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/data/ground-truth.json:795\",\n      \"iterations\": [2]\n    },\n    {\n      \"approach\": \"Make child 004 mandatory inside the structural merge without an operator scope-expansion decision\",\n      \"reason\": \"Fallback wiring is behavior expansion requiring registry/schema, caller approval, model-id normalization, and attribution changes; it is not required for the rename/nesting/reference migration.\",\n      \"evidence\": \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:42\",\n      \"iterations\": [3]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"metrics\": {\n    \"iterationsCompleted\": 3,\n    \"openQuestions\": 0,\n    \"resolvedQuestions\": 5,\n    \"keyFindings\": 8,\n    \"convergenceScore\": 0.9,\n    \"coverageBySources\": {}\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":80,"totalLines":80,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-findings-registry.json","time":{"start":1783487618504,"end":1783487618511}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_096048360aa52ef1016a4ddc8264b081919c503b1c13c5150d"}},"id":"prt_f40255dc7001E8vsOFON5bgB6Z","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffe83jWKFM65pCjvi","messageID":"msg_f40252c00001CwDalivIwjB2sT"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487618514,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffe83jWKFM65pCjvi","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_6NEyUpFHR6HrTIO1OSzlcJ6M","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":130},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Strategy - gpt55-fast-3\n2: \n3: ## 1. TOPIC\n4: Validate and stress-test the merge design for folding `deep-loop-runtime` into `deep-loop-workflows` as `system-deep-loop`: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether `fallback-router.ts` should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n5: \n6: ---\n7: \n8: <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n9: ## 2. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n10: - [x] Is the proposed `system-deep-loop/runtime/` structural layout correct, especially treating runtime as infrastructure rather than a workflow mode?\n11: - [x] Are the forward and reverse relative-path repair rules correct at concrete call sites, or do any file-depth classes break the plan?\n12: - [x] Is the `system-spec-kit` TypeScript tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped and sufficient, or does it create a silent test-coverage gap?\n13: - [x] Is the external reference migration complete and safely staged across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, and graph metadata?\n14: - [x] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, deferred, or rejected for scope/behavior reasons?\n15: <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## 3. NON-GOALS\n20: - Do not execute the merge, rename, reference rewrite, or fallback-router implementation.\n21: - Do not modify files outside this detached lineage artifact directory.\n22: - Do not evaluate historical `.opencode/specs/**` references as actionable migration targets unless they affect current routing or validation.\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: ## 4. STOP CONDITIONS\n27: - Stop after legal convergence once the five key questions have evidence-backed answers and at least three iterations are complete.\n28: - Stop at `maxIterations: 10` if convergence does not occur.\n29: - Stop early only for unrecoverable state corruption inside this lineage artifact directory.\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n34: ## 5. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n35: - Runtime should be nested under `system-deep-loop/runtime/` as infrastructure, not added to `mode-registry.json` as a workflow mode.\n36: - The path repair rule is directionally correct: runtime-to-hub shared references keep hop-count and delete the old sibling segment; workflow-to-runtime references move one hop closer and target `runtime/`.\n37: - Correction: `render-command-contract.cjs` has a `WORKSPACE_ROOT` constant that must gain one extra parent hop after nesting, just like `compile-command-contracts.cjs`.\n38: - The `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow is load-bearing because it affects runtime typecheck and council test discovery.\n39: - External reference migration is broadly complete and safely staged, provided Stage A is rerun live and historical active eval fixtures are reviewed or allowlisted instead of blindly renamed.\n40: - Fallback-router wiring should remain optional/deferred for the structural merge unless the operator explicitly expands scope to behavior changes.\n41: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n46: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n47: ## 6. WHAT WORKED\n48: - Executable import and root-depth reads exposed one concrete correction that a prose-only rename inventory could miss (iteration 1).\n49: - Category-splitting external references exposed generated-contract, advisor-corpus, plugin-fixture, agent-duplicate, and graph-edge handling differences (iteration 2).\n50: - Reading fanout runtime call sites showed fallback wiring is a broader orchestration integration problem, not only a pure-router call (iteration 3).\n51: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n56: ## 7. WHAT FAILED\n57: - Broad grep across all markdown was noisy; targeted reads of `.cjs`, `.ts`, `package.json`, and `vitest.config.ts` gave better signal (iteration 1).\n58: - Treating all non-spec old-name hits as required rewrites is unsafe; active eval fixtures may intentionally preserve historical old-name queries (iteration 2).\n59: - Treating child 004 as a one-line pool hook misses model-id normalization, approval, replacement label, and artifact-directory coupling (iteration 3).\n60: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n61: \n62: ---\n63: \n64: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n65: ## 8. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n66: [None yet]\n67: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n68: \n69: ---\n70: \n71: <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n72: ## 9. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n73: - Add `runtime/` as an eighth workflow mode: ruled out because runtime is backend infrastructure and the public mode registry already models workflow modes separately (iteration 1, evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:19`).\n74: - Blind repo-wide find/replace of old skill names: ruled out because generated contracts, advisor fields, graph edges, and historical eval fixtures need different handling (iteration 2, evidence: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/data/ground-truth.json:795`).\n75: - Make child 004 mandatory inside the structural merge without operator scope expansion: ruled out because it is behavior expansion requiring registry/schema, caller approval, model-id normalization, and attribution changes (iteration 3, evidence: `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:42`).\n76: <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n81: ## 10. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n82: [None yet]\n83: <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n88: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n89: Iteration 4: Run a synthesis-readiness/convergence pass across the answered structural, reference-migration, and fallback-scope findings; synthesize if no new contradictions appear.\n90: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n91: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n96: - `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate`.\n97: - Parent packet says the merge is structural/identity-only and excludes behavior changes, with `fallback-router.ts` scoped as optional child 004.\n98: - Child 002 plan proposes `deep-loop-workflows -> system-deep-loop`, `deep-loop-runtime -> system-deep-loop/runtime`, a single `graph-metadata.json`, forward path repair by deleting the `deep-loop-workflows` segment, and reverse path repair by reducing one `..` then renaming to `runtime`.\n99: - Child 003 plan proposes dependency-ordered external reference migration with advisor corpus baseline/regression gates.\n100: - Child 004 plan proposes optional GLM-5.2 -> MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback wiring via existing `fallback-router.ts`.\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n105: - Max iterations: 10\n106: - Minimum iterations before convergence: 3\n107: - Convergence threshold: 0.05\n108: - Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n109: - Artifact directory: `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3`\n110: - Session id: `fanout-gpt55-fast-3-1783486518892-2qss01`\n\n(End of file - total 110 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Strategy - gpt55-fast-3\n\n## 1. TOPIC\nValidate and stress-test the merge design for folding `deep-loop-runtime` into `deep-loop-workflows` as `system-deep-loop`: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether `fallback-router.ts` should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 2. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n- [x] Is the proposed `system-deep-loop/runtime/` structural layout correct, especially treating runtime as infrastructure rather than a workflow mode?\n- [x] Are the forward and reverse relative-path repair rules correct at concrete call sites, or do any file-depth classes break the plan?\n- [x] Is the `system-spec-kit` TypeScript tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped and sufficient, or does it create a silent test-coverage gap?\n- [x] Is the external reference migration complete and safely staged across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, and graph metadata?\n- [x] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, deferred, or rejected for scope/behavior reasons?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n---\n\n## 3. NON-GOALS\n- Do not execute the merge, rename, reference rewrite, or fallback-router implementation.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"# Deep Research Strategy - gpt55-fast-3\n\n## 1. TOPIC\nValidate and stress-test the merge design for folding `deep-loop-runtime` into `deep-loop-workflows` as `system-deep-loop`: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether `fallback-router.ts` should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 2. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n- [x] Is the proposed `system-deep-loop/runtime/` structural layout correct, especially treating runtime as infrastructure rather than a workflow mode?\n- [x] Are the forward and reverse relative-path repair rules correct at concrete call sites, or do any file-depth classes break the plan?\n- [x] Is the `system-spec-kit` TypeScript tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped and sufficient, or does it create a silent test-coverage gap?\n- [x] Is the external reference migration complete and safely staged across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, and graph metadata?\n- [x] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, deferred, or rejected for scope/behavior reasons?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n---\n\n## 3. NON-GOALS\n- Do not execute the merge, rename, reference rewrite, or fallback-router implementation.\n- Do not modify files outside this detached lineage artifact directory.\n- Do not evaluate historical `.opencode/specs/**` references as actionable migration targets unless they affect current routing or validation.\n\n---\n\n## 4. STOP CONDITIONS\n- Stop after legal convergence once the five key questions have evidence-backed answers and at least three iterations are complete.\n- Stop at `maxIterations: 10` if convergence does not occur.\n- Stop early only for unrecoverable state corruption inside this lineage artifact directory.\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 5. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n- Runtime should be nested under `system-deep-loop/runtime/` as infrastructure, not added to `mode-registry.json` as a workflow mode.\n- The path repair rule is directionally correct: runtime-to-hub shared references keep hop-count and delete the old sibling segment; workflow-to-runtime references move one hop closer and target `runtime/`.\n- Correction: `render-command-contract.cjs` has a `WORKSPACE_ROOT` constant that must gain one extra parent hop after nesting, just like `compile-command-contracts.cjs`.\n- The `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow is load-bearing because it affects runtime typecheck and council test discovery.\n- External reference migration is broadly complete and safely staged, provided Stage A is rerun live and historical active eval fixtures are reviewed or allowlisted instead of blindly renamed.\n- Fallback-router wiring should remain optional/deferred for the structural merge unless the operator explicitly expands scope to behavior changes.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 6. WHAT WORKED\n- Executable import and root-depth reads exposed one concrete correction that a prose-only rename inventory could miss (iteration 1).\n- Category-splitting external references exposed generated-contract, advisor-corpus, plugin-fixture, agent-duplicate, and graph-edge handling differences (iteration 2).\n- Reading fanout runtime call sites showed fallback wiring is a broader orchestration integration problem, not only a pure-router call (iteration 3).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 7. WHAT FAILED\n- Broad grep across all markdown was noisy; targeted reads of `.cjs`, `.ts`, `package.json`, and `vitest.config.ts` gave better signal (iteration 1).\n- Treating all non-spec old-name hits as required rewrites is unsafe; active eval fixtures may intentionally preserve historical old-name queries (iteration 2).\n- Treating child 004 as a one-line pool hook misses model-id normalization, approval, replacement label, and artifact-directory coupling (iteration 3).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 8. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n[None yet]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 9. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n- Add `runtime/` as an eighth workflow mode: ruled out because runtime is backend infrastructure and the public mode registry already models workflow modes separately (iteration 1, evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:19`).\n- Blind repo-wide find/replace of old skill names: ruled out because generated contracts, advisor fields, graph edges, and historical eval fixtures need different handling (iteration 2, evidence: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/data/ground-truth.json:795`).\n- Make child 004 mandatory inside the structural merge without operator scope expansion: ruled out because it is behavior expansion requiring registry/schema, caller approval, model-id normalization, and attribution changes (iteration 3, evidence: `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:42`).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 10. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n[None yet]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\nIteration 4: Run a synthesis-readiness/convergence pass across the answered structural, reference-migration, and fallback-scope findings; synthesize if no new contradictions appear.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n- `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate`.\n- Parent packet says the merge is structural/identity-only and excludes behavior changes, with `fallback-router.ts` scoped as optional child 004.\n- Child 002 plan proposes `deep-loop-workflows -> system-deep-loop`, `deep-loop-runtime -> system-deep-loop/runtime`, a single `graph-metadata.json`, forward path repair by deleting the `deep-loop-workflows` segment, and reverse path repair by reducing one `..` then renaming to `runtime`.\n- Child 003 plan proposes dependency-ordered external reference migration with advisor corpus baseline/regression gates.\n- Child 004 plan proposes optional GLM-5.2 -> MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback wiring via existing `fallback-router.ts`.\n\n---\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n- Max iterations: 10\n- Minimum iterations before convergence: 3\n- Convergence threshold: 0.05\n- Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n- Artifact directory: `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3`\n- Session id: `fanout-gpt55-fast-3-1783486518892-2qss01`","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":110,"totalLines":110,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1783487618508,"end":1783487618512}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_096048360aa52ef1016a4ddc8264c0819194608b4293015784"}},"id":"prt_f40255dcb001EQw86w1L6AClHq","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffe83jWKFM65pCjvi","messageID":"msg_f40252c00001CwDalivIwjB2sT"}}
