{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487816733,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66ceffe83jWKFM65pCjvi","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_tnMi9c1qFbPNllqyaMrBGXl4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/prompts/iteration-004.md\n+STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n+Segment: 1 | Iteration: 4 of 10\n+Questions: 5/5 answered | Last focus: Fallback-router wiring scope\n+Last 2 ratios: 0.72 -> 0.44 | Stuck count: 0\n+Resource map: resource-map.md not present at init; skipping source coverage gate. Artifact resource-map emission remains enabled.\n+Memory context refresh: none loaded yet.\n+Next focus: Synthesis-readiness convergence pass across the answered structural, reference-migration, and fallback-scope findings.\n+\n+Research Topic: Validate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop.\n+Focus Area: Final contradiction check against parent and child phase specs, convergence legality, and synthesis readiness.\n+State Files:\n+- Config: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-config.json\n+- State: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-state.jsonl\n+- Strategy: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n+- Output: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/iterations/iteration-004.md\n+\n+CONSTRAINT: LEAF research iteration; do not dispatch sub-agents and do not write outside the lineage artifact directory.\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/iterations/iteration-004.md\n+# Iteration 4: Synthesis-Readiness Convergence Pass\n+\n+## Focus\n+Run a final contradiction check across the parent packet, child 001-005 specs/plans, and deep-research stop contract to decide whether this lineage can legally synthesize.\n+\n+## Findings\n+\n+1. Parent scope confirms the structural/identity framing and supports deferring fallback behavior. The parent explicitly includes physical merge, bidirectional path repair, external reference migration, and version/graph consolidation [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/spec.md:73] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/spec.md:77], while out-of-scope items include changing loop/fanout behavior and fully wiring `fallback-router.ts` [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/spec.md:80] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/spec.md:83]. This confirms iteration 3's recommendation: child 004 can remain optional unless the operator expands scope.\n+\n+2. Child 002 is directionally sound but should be amended with the render-command-contract root-depth correction before implementation starts. Its plan already separates forward same-hop path deletion from reverse one-hop-shorter runtime references [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:68] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:78]. It also includes `render-command-contract.cjs`'s shared-rollout require and `compile-command-contracts.cjs`'s `WORKSPACE_ROOT` anchor [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:72] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:73]. Iteration 1 found that `render-command-contract.cjs` has its own `WORKSPACE_ROOT` constant at line 13, so Stage 3a should add that to the concrete site table before execution [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs:13].\n+\n+3. Child 003 is directionally sound but its residual-grep rule needs one allowlist refinement. The plan rejects blind one-shot replacement and stages code constants, codegen, generated contracts, agents, graph metadata, and advisor corpus in a safe order [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:66] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:75] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:89] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:101]. But it currently says anything executable, structured-data, or advisor-facing must update, with only `.opencode/specs/**` historical references safe to leave [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:67]. Iteration 2 found active `system-spec-kit` eval fixtures that intentionally contain historical old-name queries/decoys, so Stage J should include a reviewed allowlist for semantically historical active eval data [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/data/ground-truth.json:795] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/data/ground-truth.json:960].\n+\n+4. Child 005's closeout dependency model is consistent with the research result. Its readiness gate requires 002 and 003, and 004 only if in scope [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/005-validation-and-closeout/plan.md:51] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/005-validation-and-closeout/plan.md:52]. That matches this lineage's recommendation to run 001 -> 002 -> 003 -> 005, with 004 optional/deferred.\n+\n+5. Deep-research legal stop is satisfied. The stop contract says hard stops include all key questions answered [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md:49] and the live algorithm nominates STOP once all key questions have evidence-backed answers [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md:91] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md:92]. This lineage has completed 4 iterations, exceeding the minimum floor of 3 recorded in config, and all 5 key questions are answered in strategy and registry.\n+\n+## Sources Consulted\n+- `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/spec.md`\n+- `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md`\n+- `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md`\n+- `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md`\n+- `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/{spec.md,plan.md,tasks.md}`\n+- `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/005-validation-and-closeout/plan.md`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md`\n+- Prior iteration artifacts in this lineage.\n+\n+## Assessment\n+- newInfoRatio: 0.03\n+- Novelty justification: No new contradictions; only synthesis-level restatement of two concrete child-plan amendments already discovered in iterations 1 and 2.\n+- Confidence: High that this lineage can synthesize with `stopReason: converged`.\n+\n+## Reflection\n+- What worked: Cross-checking parent scope against child 004 removed ambiguity about fallback behavior being optional.\n+- What failed: No additional gaps surfaced in the convergence pass.\n+- Ruled out: Continuing to a fifth iteration; all key questions are answered, minimum floor is met, and the last pass produced no new contradictions.\n+\n+## Recommended Next Focus\n+Synthesize final `research.md`, emit artifact `resource-map.md`, mark config complete, and append `synthesis_complete`.\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deltas/iter-004.jsonl\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":4,\"run\":4,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Synthesis-readiness convergence pass\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.03,\"noveltyJustification\":\"No new contradictions; confirmed parent/child phase consistency and two existing amendment requirements before synthesis.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Can this lineage legally synthesize after answering all five key questions and meeting the minimum iteration floor?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Yes. All five key questions are evidence-backed, the lineage completed four iterations, and parent/child specs are consistent with the recommended sequence and optional 004 deferral.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"f020-parent-scope-confirms-defer-004\",\"summary\":\"Parent scope explicitly excludes fanout behavior changes and tracks fallback-router wiring as optional/operator-gated.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/spec.md:80\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/spec.md:83\"]},{\"id\":\"f021-child-002-needs-render-root-depth-amendment\",\"summary\":\"Child 002's path plan is directionally correct but should add render-command-contract.cjs WORKSPACE_ROOT depth repair before implementation.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:72\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs:13\"]},{\"id\":\"f022-child-003-needs-eval-allowlist-amendment\",\"summary\":\"Child 003's residual-grep stage needs a reviewed allowlist for semantically historical active eval fixtures.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:67\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/data/ground-truth.json:795\"]},{\"id\":\"f023-child-005-sequence-consistent\",\"summary\":\"Child 005 already treats 004 as conditional, so the recommended sequence is 001 -> 002 -> 003 -> 005 unless 004 is explicitly scoped in.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/005-validation-and-closeout/plan.md:51\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/005-validation-and-closeout/plan.md:52\"]},{\"id\":\"f024-legal-stop-satisfied\",\"summary\":\"Deep-research stop contract permits convergence when all key questions are evidence-backed after the minimum floor.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md:49\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md:91\"]}],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Continue to a fifth iteration\",\"reason\":\"All key questions are answered, the minimum floor is met, and the convergence pass produced no new contradictions.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md:49\"}],\"recommendedNextFocus\":\"Synthesize final research.md and close lineage state.\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:13:44Z\",\"durationMs\":230000,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-3-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/research.md\n+# Deep-Loop Unification Research Synthesis - gpt55-fast-3\n+\n+## 1. Executive Summary\n+This lineage confirms the proposed `system-deep-loop` unification is viable as a structural/identity merge, with two required plan amendments before implementation: add `render-command-contract.cjs`'s own `WORKSPACE_ROOT` depth repair to child 002, and add a reviewed allowlist for semantically historical active eval fixtures to child 003. Fallback-router wiring should remain optional/deferred unless the operator explicitly expands scope to behavior changes.\n+\n+## 2. Research Scope\n+The run investigated structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling, the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow, external reference migration, and whether GLM-5.2 to MiMo-V2.5-Pro fallback should be wired during this packet. It did not execute the merge, rewrite references, or modify source code outside this lineage artifact directory.\n+\n+## 3. Method\n+Four iterations inspected source files, tests, command assets, advisor corpus surfaces, spec plans, and deep-research stop-contract references. Each iteration wrote a narrative, JSONL delta, and append-only state record, then was verified with `verify-iteration.cjs`.\n+\n+## 4. Evidence Base\n+- Iteration 1: structural layout and bidirectional path repairs.\n+- Iteration 2: external reference migration categories.\n+- Iteration 3: fallback-router wiring scope.\n+- Iteration 4: synthesis-readiness convergence pass.\n+- Verification: `verify-iteration.cjs` passed for iterations 1, 2, and 3 before synthesis; iteration 4 verification is expected as the final pre-close gate.\n+\n+## 5. Structural Layout Finding\n+`system-deep-loop/runtime/` should remain infrastructure, not become an eighth workflow mode. The existing workflow hub routes modes through `mode-registry.json`, while runtime modules are backend support for research/review/council/improvement. Adding runtime as a mode would blur workflow and infrastructure boundaries.\n+\n+Evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:12`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:19`.\n+\n+## 6. Path-Coupling Finding\n+The bidirectional path-repair rule is correct:\n+\n+- Runtime-to-hub shared references keep hop-count and delete the old `deep-loop-workflows` segment.\n+- Workflow-to-runtime references move one hop closer and target `runtime/`.\n+\n+Required amendment: child 002 already covers `compile-command-contracts.cjs` root-depth repair, but must also include `render-command-contract.cjs`'s `WORKSPACE_ROOT` constant.\n+\n+Evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs:13`, `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:72`.\n+\n+## 7. Tooling-Borrow Finding\n+The `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow is load-bearing and belongs in child 002. Runtime typecheck and `system-spec-kit` council test discovery both depend on current relative paths. Deferring these edits to external reference migration would create a silent coverage risk.\n+\n+Evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/package.json:10`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts:18`.\n+\n+## 8. External Migration Finding\n+Child 003's staged migration model is correct: code constants, generated contracts, duplicated agents, plugin/test fixtures, advisor corpus, graph metadata, and docs need category-specific handling rather than blind replacement. Compiled `/deep` contracts must be regenerated, not hand-edited.\n+\n+Required amendment: residual grep must allow reviewed exceptions for active eval fixtures that intentionally preserve historical old-name queries/decoys.\n+\n+Evidence: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_research.contract.md:1`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/data/ground-truth.json:795`.\n+\n+## 9. Fallback-Router Finding\n+`fallback-router.ts` is a real, tested decision primitive but has no production dispatch caller. Current fanout behavior retries the same lineage label/model until `maxRetries` exhaustion, then records `retry_exhausted`; it does not swap models.\n+\n+Fallback wiring should remain optional/deferred because it is behavior expansion requiring registry/schema work, canonical-id to provider-slug normalization, explicit caller approval, a `fanout-run.cjs` integration point, and separate fallback lineage attribution.\n+\n+Evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:357`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:628`, `.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:269`.\n+\n+## 10. Plan Revisions\n+Before child 002 starts:\n+\n+- Add `render-command-contract.cjs` `WORKSPACE_ROOT` depth repair to the concrete path table.\n+\n+Before child 003 starts:\n+\n+- Treat Stage A's fresh live inventory as authoritative.\n+- Add a residual-grep allowlist/review path for semantically historical active eval fixtures.\n+- Keep generated contract handling regenerate-only.\n+\n+Before child 004 starts, if scoped in:\n+\n+- Revise it from a pool-only hook to a real fanout integration design covering model registry, approval, slug normalization, fallback labels, and integration tests.\n+\n+## 11. Recommendations\n+Proceed with child 002 after applying the `render-command-contract.cjs` amendment, then child 003 after adding the eval-fixture allowlist rule. Run child 005 closeout after 002 and 003 pass their gates. Do not include child 004 unless the operator explicitly chooses to expand this packet beyond structural unification.\n+\n+## Eliminated Alternatives\n+| Approach | Reason Eliminated | Evidence | Iteration(s) |\n+|---|---|---|---|\n+| Add `runtime/` as a workflow mode | Runtime is backend infrastructure; workflow modes are separately modeled in `mode-registry.json`. | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:19` | 1 |\n+| Blind repo-wide find/replace | Generated contracts, advisor fields, graph edges, and historical eval fixtures need different handling. | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/data/ground-truth.json:795` | 2 |\n+| Make child 004 mandatory in the structural merge | It is behavior expansion requiring registry/schema, approval, model-id normalization, and attribution changes. | `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:42` | 3 |\n+| Continue to a fifth iteration | All key questions are answered, the minimum floor is met, and the convergence pass produced no new contradictions. | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md:49` | 4 |\n+\n+## 12. Open Questions\n+No blocking questions remain for this lineage. The only operator decision is whether to scope child 004 into the packet; the research recommendation is to defer it.\n+\n+## 13. Risks\n+- Naive path-depth repair can break one direction of coupling while fixing the other.\n+- Residual grep without semantic review can corrupt active historical eval fixtures.\n+- Fallback wiring can silently mix GLM and MiMo artifacts if it reuses the same lineage label.\n+\n+## 14. Confidence\n+High confidence on structural layout, path-rule direction, tooling-borrow scope, external migration categories, and 004 deferral. Medium confidence on exact fallback implementation shape because no code was changed or tested for that optional phase.\n+\n+## 15. Verification Notes\n+- Iteration 1 verified with `verify-iteration.cjs`: passed.\n+- Iteration 2 verified with `verify-iteration.cjs`: passed.\n+- Iteration 3 verified with `verify-iteration.cjs`: passed.\n+- Iteration 4 and final synthesis require the closing verification commands after these artifacts are written.\n+\n+## 16. Resource Map\n+The source `resource-map.md` was absent at init, so the coverage gate was skipped. This lineage emits a compact artifact `resource-map.md` summarizing the files actually used.\n+\n+## 17. References\n+- `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/spec.md`\n+- `.opencode/specs/system-d