,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T04:58:44Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-3-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":1,\"run\":1,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Structural layout and bidirectional path-coupling repair\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.86,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Mostly confirmed the candidate layout and path rules, while adding a concrete missed WORKSPACE_ROOT repair in render-command-contract.cjs.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Is the proposed system-deep-loop/runtime structural layout correct?\",\"Are forward and reverse path-coupling repair rules correct at concrete call sites?\",\"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow repair correctly scoped and sufficient?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"The runtime-as-infrastructure layout is correct and should not become a workflow mode.\",\"The asymmetric path rule is correct, with one added root-depth repair for render-command-contract.cjs.\",\"The system-spec-kit tooling-borrow is load-bearing and belongs in the structural phase.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"f001-runtime-not-mode\",\"summary\":\"system-deep-loop/runtime should remain infrastructure, not a workflow mode.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:12\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:19\"]},{\"id\":\"f002-forward-rule-mostly-correct\",\"summary\":\"Forward runtime-to-hub shared references keep hop-count and delete the old sibling segment.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs:8\"]},{\"id\":\"f003-render-root-depth-missed\",\"summary\":\"render-command-contract.cjs has a WORKSPACE_ROOT depth constant that must gain one more parent hop after nesting.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs:13\"]},{\"id\":\"f004-reverse-rule-confirmed\",\"summary\":\"Workflow packet code moves one hop closer to runtime and should target ../../runtime or ../../../runtime depending on nested depth.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:14\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs:122\"]},{\"id\":\"f005-tooling-borrow-load-bearing\",\"summary\":\"Runtime typecheck and system-spec-kit council test discovery both rely on deep-loop-runtime paths and must be repaired in the structural phase.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/package.json:10\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts:18\"]}],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Add runtime as a workflow mode\",\"reason\":\"The live registry treats runtime as backendKind/runtimeLoopType infrastructure, while user-facing modes remain research/review/council/improvement.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:19\"}],\"recommendedNextFocus\":\"Inventory external reference migration categories and stress-test child 003 coverage.\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:01:18Z\",\"durationMs\":377000,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-3-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":2,\"run\":2,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"External reference migration coverage\",\"findingsCount\":7,\"newInfoRatio\":0.72,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Confirmed most migration categories and added two refinements: fresh Stage-A baseline authority and explicit allowlisting for historical active eval fixtures.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Is external reference migration complete and safely staged across commands, agents, READMEs, hooks, advisor corpus, and graph metadata?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"External reference migration is broadly complete and safely staged if Stage A is treated as authoritative and historical eval fixtures are reviewed or allowlisted instead of blindly renamed.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"f006-stage-a-live-baseline\",\"summary\":\"Live old-name inventory differs from the spec count; Stage A must capture the authoritative baseline immediately before edits.\",\"sources\":[\"command: rg-count sweep 2026-07-08T05:02Z\"]},{\"id\":\"f007-compiled-contracts-regenerate-only\",\"summary\":\"Compiled /deep command contracts embed generated headers, source digests, and old paths, so they must be regenerated rather than hand-edited.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_research.contract.md:1\",\".opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_research.contract.md:6\"]},{\"id\":\"f008-advisor-field-scope\",\"summary\":\"Advisor constants and routing fixtures require field-scoped migration plus accuracy re-baseline.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:83\",\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:109\"]},{\"id\":\"f009-plugin-fixture-pair\",\"summary\":\"mk-deep-loop-guard's registry path and test fixture must update together.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js:35\",\".opencode/plugins/tests/mk-deep-loop-guard.test.cjs:25\"]},{\"id\":\"f010-agent-duplicate-trees\",\"summary\":\"Both .opencode and .claude agent trees carry real old references and must be edited in lockstep.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/agents/orchestrate.md:185\",\".claude/agents/orchestrate.md:174\"]},{\"id\":\"f011-eval-fixture-allowlist\",\"summary\":\"Active system-spec-kit eval fixtures intentionally contain historical old-name queries/decoys and should be reviewed or allowlisted, not blindly renamed.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/data/ground-truth.json:795\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/data/ground-truth.json:960\"]},{\"id\":\"f012-graph-edge-collapse\",\"summary\":\"Sibling graph metadata needs edge collapse from two old identities to one system-deep-loop identity.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/graph-metadata.json:35\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/graph-metadata.json:40\"]}],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Blind repo-wide find/replace of old skill names\",\"reason\":\"Generated contracts, advisor fields, graph edges, and historical eval fixtures need different handling.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/data/ground-truth.json:795\"}],\"recommendedNextFocus\":\"Evaluate fallback-router.ts and current fanout retry behavior.\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:05:18Z\",\"durationMs\":520000,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-3-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":3,\"run\":3,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Fallback-router wiring scope\",\"findingsCount\":7,\"newInfoRatio\":0.44,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Confirmed the zero-caller gap and added implementation blockers: narrow call-site assumption, missing registry edge, canonical-id/provider-slug mapping, approval policy, and fallback-label attribution.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Should fallback-router.ts be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Fallback-router wiring should remain optional/deferred for the structural merge unless the operator explicitly expands scope to behavior changes.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"f013-fallback-zero-production-caller\",\"summary\":\"fallback-router.ts is a shipped pure decision primitive with test-only callers and no production dispatch integration.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:357\",\"grep resolveFallback/createFallbackRouter 2026-07-08T05:08Z\"]},{\"id\":\"f014-fanout-same-label-retry\",\"summary\":\"fanout-pool retries the same item/index/label until maxRetries and then sets retry_exhausted; no model-swap path exists.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:628\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:650\"]},{\"id\":\"f015-fallback-callsite-too-narrow\",\"summary\":\"Child 004's proposed fanout-pool-only call site is too narrow because fanout-run owns model-bearing lineages, prompt construction, command dispatch, and artifact validation.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/plan.md:90\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1534\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1599\"]},{\"id\":\"f016-glm-mimo-edge-not-configured\",\"summary\":\"The current model profile registry lists both GLM-5.2 and MiMo-V2.5-Pro with fallback_target null, so GLM-to-MiMo fallback would be new policy/configuration.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:204\",\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:269\"]},{\"id\":\"f017-model-id-normalization-needed\",\"summary\":\"Fallback router ids differ from executable provider slugs, so integration needs canonical-id to CLI-slug normalization.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:207\",\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:272\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1349\"]},{\"id\":\"f018-fallback-approval-required\",\"summary\":\"The fallback router's approved-model guard means substitution must be explicitly approved by config/policy, not silently inferred from a global edge.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:411\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/executor-provenance-mismatch.vitest.ts:252\"]},{\"id\":\"f019-fallback-label-attribution\",\"summary\":\"A fallback lineage needs a distinct label/artifact directory and status event to avoid mixing failed GLM retry state with MiMo replacement output.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1553\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:783\"]}],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Make child 004 mandatory inside the structural merge without an operator scope-expansion decision\",\"reason\":\"Fallback wiring is behavior expansion requiring registry/schema, caller approval, model-id normalization, and attribution changes; it is not required for the rename/nesting/reference migration.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:42\"}],\"recommendedNextFocus\":\"Run synthesis-readiness/convergence pass and produce final research synthesis if no contradictions appear.\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:09:54Z\",\"durationMs\":276000,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-3-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":4,\"run\":4,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Synthesis-readiness convergence pass\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.03,\"noveltyJustification\":\"No new contradictions; confirmed parent/child phase consistency and two existing amendment requirements before synthesis.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Can this lineage legally synthesize after answering all five key questions and meeting the minimum iteration floor?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Yes. All five key questions are evidence-backed, the lineage completed four iterations, and parent/child specs are consistent with the recommended sequence and optional 004 deferral.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"f020-parent-scope-confirms-defer-004\",\"summary\":\"Parent scope explicitly excludes fanout behavior changes and tracks fallback-router wiring as optional/operator-gated.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/spec.md:80\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/spec.md:83\"]},{\"id\":\"f021-child-002-needs-render-root-depth-amendment\",\"summary\":\"Child 002's path plan is directionally correct but should add render-command-contract.cjs WORKSPACE_ROOT depth repair before implementation.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:72\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs:13\"]},{\"id\":\"f022-child-003-needs-eval-allowlist-amendment\",\"summary\":\"Child 003's residual-grep stage needs a reviewed allowlist for semantically historical active eval fixtures.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:67\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/data/ground-truth.json:795\"]},{\"id\":\"f023-child-005-sequence-consistent\",\"summary\":\"Child 005 already treats 004 as conditional, so the recommended sequence is 001 -> 002 -> 003 -> 005 unless 004 is explicitly scoped in.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/005-validation-and-closeout/plan.md:51\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/005-validation-and-closeout/plan.md:52\"]},{\"id\":\"f024-legal-stop-satisfied\",\"summary\":\"Deep-research stop contract permits convergence when all key questions are evidence-backed after the minimum floor.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md:49\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md:91\"]}],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Continue to a fifth iteration\",\"reason\":\"All key questions are answered, the minimum floor is met, and the convergence pass produced no new contradictions.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md:49\"}],\"recommendedNextFocus\":\"Synthesize final research.md and close lineage state.\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:13:44Z\",\"durationMs\":230000,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-3-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"totalIterations\":4,\"answeredCount\":5,\"totalQuestions\":5,\"stopReason\":\"converged\",\"researchPath\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/research.md\",\"resourceMapPath\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/resource-map.md\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:13:44Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-3-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -37,8 +37,9 @@\n - Correction: `render-command-contract.cjs` has a `WORKSPACE_ROOT` constant that must gain one extra parent hop after nesting, just like `compile-command-contracts.cjs`.\n - The `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow is load-bearing because it affects runtime typecheck and council test discovery.\n - External reference migration is broadly complete and safely staged, provided Stage A is rerun live and historical active eval fixtures are reviewed or allowlisted instead of blindly renamed.\n - Fallback-router wiring should remain optional/deferred for the structural merge unless the operator explicitly expands scope to behavior changes.\n+- Convergence pass found no new contradictions; child 002/003 need the two listed amendments before implementation, and child 004 remains optional.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n \n ---\n \n@@ -47,8 +48,9 @@\n ## 6. WHAT WORKED\n - Executable import and root-depth reads exposed one concrete correction that a prose-only rename inventory could miss (iteration 1).\n - Category-splitting external references exposed generated-contract, advisor-corpus, plugin-fixture, agent-duplicate, and graph-edge handling differences (iteration 2).\n - Reading fanout runtime call sites showed fallback wiring is a broader orchestration integration problem, not only a pure-router call (iteration 3).\n+- Parent/child spec cross-check confirmed the recommended sequence and did not reveal new contradictions (iteration 4).\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n \n ---\n \n@@ -56,8 +58,9 @@\n ## 7. WHAT FAILED\n - Broad grep across all markdown was noisy; targeted reads of `.cjs`, `.ts`, `package.json`, and `vitest.config.ts` gave better signal (iteration 1).\n - Treating all non-spec old-name hits as required rewrites is unsafe; active eval fixtures may intentionally preserve historical old-name queries (iteration 2).\n - Treating child 004 as a one-line pool hook misses model-id normalization, approval, replacement label, and artifact-directory coupling (iteration 3).\n+- No additional gaps surfaced during synthesis-readiness pass (iteration 4).\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n \n ---\n \n@@ -72,8 +75,9 @@\n ## 9. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n - Add `runtime/` as an eighth workflow mode: ruled out because runtime is backend infrastructure and the public mode registry already models workflow modes separately (iteration 1, evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:19`).\n - Blind repo-wide find/replace of old skill names: ruled out because generated contracts, advisor fields, graph edges, and historical eval fixtures need different handling (iteration 2, evidence: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/eval/data/ground-truth.json:795`).\n - Make child 004 mandatory inside the structural merge without operator scope expansion: ruled out because it is behavior expansion requiring registry/schema, caller approval, model-id normalization, and attribution changes (iteration 3, evidence: `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:42`).\n+- Continue to a fifth iteration: ruled out because all key questions are answered, the minimum floor is met, and the convergence pass produced no new contradictions (iteration 4, evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md:49`).\n <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n \n ---\n \n@@ -85,9 +89,9 @@\n ---\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n-Iteration 4: Run a synthesis-readiness/convergence pass across the answered structural, reference-migration, and fallback-scope findings; synthesize if no new contradictions appear.\n+Complete: final synthesis written to `research.md`; artifact `resource-map.md` emitted; stopReason=`converged`.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ---\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep